Note:
This file handles IR optimization and code optimization passes.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process IR optimization and code optimization passes
- Handle optimization pass selection and optimization pass execution
- Manage optimization validation and optimization verification
- Process optimization debugging and optimization analysis

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- IR optimization enables high-performance code generation
- Proper optimization handling ensures optimal code performance
- IR optimization support enables Runa compilation for performance-optimized code generation

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- IR optimization and code optimization passes
- Optimization pass selection and optimization pass execution
- Optimization validation and optimization verification
- Optimization debugging and optimization analysis

Dependencies:
- Imports MIR for mid-level IR representation
- Imports CFG for control flow analysis
- Imports dominance for dominance analysis
- Imports data_flow for dataflow analysis
- Imports call_graph for inter-procedural analysis
- Imports profile_guided for PGO data
- Imports alias_analysis for memory analysis
- Imports memory/layout.runa for OWNED HEAP allocation (Tier 3)
- Imports collections for data structure management
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/mir.runa" as MIR
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/cfg.runa" as CFG
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/dominance.runa" as Dominance
Import "compiler/middle/analysis/data_flow.runa" as DataFlow
Import "compiler/middle/analysis/control_flow.runa" as ControlFlow
Import "compiler/middle/analysis/call_graph.runa" as CallGraph
Import "compiler/middle/analysis/profile_guided.runa" as ProfileGuided
Import "compiler/middle/analysis/alias_analysis.runa" as AliasAnalysis
Import "compiler/middle/analysis/points_to.runa" as PointsTo
Import "compiler/middle/lto/whole_program_analysis.runa" as WholeProgramAnalysis
Import "compiler/middle/lto/cross_module_optimization.runa" as CrossModuleOptimization
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as MemoryCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dictionary
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/set.runa" as Set
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/io/display.runa" as Display

Note: ============================================================================
Note: OptimizationContext - Main context for optimization passes
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
The OptimizationContext maintains all state needed during optimization:
- MIR function being optimized
- Analysis results (dataflow, dominance, alias analysis)
- Optimization settings and flags
- Statistics tracking
- Use-def chains and def-use chains
- Value numbering maps
- Loop information
- Profile-guided optimization data

This allows optimization passes to share analysis results and avoid recomputation.

Memory Layout (136 bytes, Tier 3: OWNED HEAP):
Offset  Size  Field                    Description
------  ----  -----                    -----------
0       8     mir_function             Pointer to MIR function being optimized
8       8     cfg                      Pointer to control flow graph
16      8     dominance_info           Pointer to dominance analysis results
24      8     dataflow_info            Pointer to dataflow analysis results
32      8     alias_info               Pointer to alias analysis results
40      8     loop_info                Pointer to loop analysis results
48      8     use_def_chains           Dictionary mapping uses to definitions
56      8     def_use_chains           Dictionary mapping definitions to uses
64      8     value_numbers            Dictionary for global value numbering
72      8     constant_values          Dictionary of known constant values
80      4     changed                  1 if any optimization made changes, 0 otherwise
84      4     optimization_level       Optimization level (0=none, 1=O1, 2=O2, 3=O3)
88      8     profile_data             Pointer to PGO data (if available)
96      8     inlining_candidates      List of functions eligible for inlining
104     8     dead_instructions        Set of instructions marked for deletion
112     4     instruction_count        Total instruction count
116     4     basic_block_count        Total basic block count
120     8     statistics               Pointer to optimization statistics
128     8     pga                      Pointer to ProfileGuidedAnalysis (PGO workspace,
                                       set by apply_profile_guided_optimizations,
                                       0 when PGO has not run for this function)
@End Reasoning

Type called "OptimizationContext":
    mir_function as Integer
    cfg as Integer
    dominance_info as Integer
    dataflow_info as Integer
    alias_info as Integer
    loop_info as Integer
    use_def_chains as Integer
    def_use_chains as Integer
    value_numbers as Integer
    constant_values as Integer
    changed as Integer
    optimization_level as Integer
    profile_data as Integer
    inlining_candidates as Integer
    dead_instructions as Integer
    instruction_count as Integer
    basic_block_count as Integer
    statistics as Integer
    pga as Integer
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: OptimizationPass - Descriptor for optimization pass
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
OptimizationPass describes metadata about an optimization pass:
- Pass name and description
- Dependencies on other passes
- Whether it preserves CFG structure
- Whether it requires specific analyses
- Cost-benefit metrics

Memory Layout (96 bytes, Tier 3: OWNED HEAP):
Offset  Size  Field                    Description
------  ----  -----                    -----------
0       8     pass_name                Name of optimization pass
8       8     pass_function            Function pointer to pass implementation
16      4     requires_ssa             1 if requires SSA form, 0 otherwise
20      4     preserves_cfg            1 if preserves CFG structure, 0 otherwise
24      4     is_analysis_pass         1 if analysis only (no transformation)
28      4     optimization_level       Minimum opt level (0, 1, 2, or 3)
32      8     required_analyses        List of required analysis passes
40      8     invalidated_analyses     List of analyses invalidated by this pass
48      8     statistics               Pass execution statistics
56      4     iterations_run           Number of multiplied by this pass was run
60      4     transformations_applied  Number of transformations applied
64      8     execution_time           Time spent in this pass (microseconds)
72      8     pass_description         Human-readable description
80      16    reserved                 Reserved for future use
@End Reasoning

Type called "OptimizationPass":
    pass_name as Integer
    pass_function as Integer
    requires_ssa as Integer
    preserves_cfg as Integer
    is_analysis_pass as Integer
    optimization_level as Integer
    required_analyses as Integer
    invalidated_analyses as Integer
    statistics as Integer
    iterations_run as Integer
    transformations_applied as Integer
    execution_time as Integer
    pass_description as Integer
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: UseDefChain - Use-definition chain for SSA values
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
UseDefChain tracks the relationship between value uses and their definitions.
This is essential for:
- Constant propagation
- Copy propagation
- Dead code elimination
- Value numbering

Memory Layout (64 bytes, Tier 3: OWNED HEAP):
Offset  Size  Field                    Description
------  ----  -----                    -----------
0       4     value_id                 SSA value ID
4       4     definition_type          Definition type (instruction opcode)
8       8     defining_instruction     Pointer to instruction that defines this value
16      8     defining_block           Basic block containing definition
24      8     uses                     List of instructions that use this value
32      8     use_blocks               List of blocks where value is used
40      4     use_count                Number of uses of this value
44      4     is_constant              1 if value is compile-time constant, 0 otherwise
48      8     constant_value           Constant value (if is_constant == 1)
56      8     reaching_definitions     Set of definitions that reach uses
@End Reasoning

Type called "UseDefChain":
    value_id as Integer
    definition_type as Integer
    defining_instruction as Integer
    defining_block as Integer
    uses as Integer
    use_blocks as Integer
    use_count as Integer
    is_constant as Integer
    constant_value as Integer
    reaching_definitions as Integer
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Optimization Level Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Constant OPT_LEVEL_O0 as Integer is 0       Note: No optimization (named O0 to match the O1/O2/O3 family; the backend interface owns the OPT_LEVEL_NONE name)
Constant OPT_LEVEL_O1 as Integer is 1       Note: Basic optimizations
Constant OPT_LEVEL_O2 as Integer is 2       Note: Moderate optimizations
Constant OPT_LEVEL_O3 as Integer is 3       Note: Aggressive optimizations

Note: ============================================================================
Note: create_optimization_context - Create optimization context
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Creates and initializes an OptimizationContext for a MIR function.
Runs necessary analyses and builds data structures for optimization passes.
@End Reasoning

Process called "create_optimization_context" that takes mir_func as Integer, opt_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Allocate OptimizationContext structure (136 bytes - was 128
    Note: before the PGA field at offset 128 was added).
    Let ctx be proc allocate from Layout with 136

    Note: Initialize MIR function pointer
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 0, mir_func

    Note: Get CFG from MIR function
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with mir_func, 32
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8, cfg

    Note: Compute dominance information
    Let dominance_info be proc compute_dominance_tree from Dominance with cfg
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 16, dominance_info

    Note: Compute dataflow information: live-variable analysis over the
    Note: function's CFG. The result is the liveness-info list produced by
    Note: the data-flow module's backward fixpoint solver.
    Let dataflow_info be proc compute_live_variables_mir from DataFlow with cfg
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 24, dataflow_info

    Note: Compute alias analysis if opt level >= O2. Alias analysis is
    Note: built on Andersen points-to results: build the function's
    Note: points-to graph, extract its constraints, solve them, then wrap
    Note: the solved graph in an AliasAnalysis handle and compute the
    Note: per-function mod/ref summary.
    Let alias_info be 0
    If opt_level is greater than or equal to 2:
        Let pts_graph be proc create_points_to_graph from PointsTo
        If pts_graph is not equal to 0:
            proc extract_constraints_from_mir from PointsTo with pts_graph, mir_func
            proc compute_points_to_andersen from PointsTo with pts_graph
            Set alias_info to proc create_alias_analysis from AliasAnalysis with pts_graph
            If alias_info is not equal to 0:
                proc compute_mod_ref from AliasAnalysis with alias_info, mir_func
            End If
        End If
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 32, alias_info

    Note: Initialize loop info to 0 (will be computed on demand)
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 40, 0

    Note: Create use-def chains
    Let use_def_chains be proc create from Dictionary
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 48, use_def_chains

    Note: Create def-use chains
    Let def_use_chains be proc create from Dictionary
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 56, def_use_chains

    Note: Build use-def chains
    build_use_def_chains(ctx)

    Note: Create value numbering map
    Let value_numbers be proc create from Dictionary
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 64, value_numbers

    Note: Create constant values map
    Let constant_values be proc create from Dictionary
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 72, constant_values

    Note: Initialize changed flag to 0
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with ctx, 80, 0

    Note: Set optimization level
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with ctx, 84, opt_level

    Note: Initialize profile data to 0 (can be set later)
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 88, 0

    Note: Create inlining candidates list
    Let inlining_candidates be proc list_create from List
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 96, inlining_candidates

    Note: Create dead instructions set
    Let dead_instructions be proc create from Dictionary
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 104, dead_instructions

    Note: Count instructions and blocks
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with ctx, 116, block_count

    Let total_instructions be count_total_instructions(blocks)
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with ctx, 112, total_instructions

    Note: Create statistics structure
    Let statistics be create_optimization_statistics()
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 120, statistics

    Note: Initialize PGA pointer to 0 (set later by
    Note: apply_profile_guided_optimizations when profile data is present).
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 128, 0

    Return ctx
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: count_total_instructions - Count total instructions in function
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "count_total_instructions" that takes blocks as Integer returns Integer:
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks
    Let total be 0

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
        Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions
        Set total to total plus inst_count
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return total
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: create_optimization_statistics - Create statistics tracker
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "create_optimization_statistics" returns Integer:
    Note: Allocate statistics structure (128 bytes)
    Let stats be proc allocate from Layout with 128

    Note: Initialize all counters to 0
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with stats, 0, 0 Note: dead_code_eliminated
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with stats, 4, 0 Note: constants_folded
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with stats, 8, 0 Note: constants_propagated
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with stats, 12, 0 Note: copies_propagated
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with stats, 16, 0 Note: cse_eliminations
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with stats, 20, 0 Note: functions_inlined
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with stats, 24, 0 Note: loops_unrolled
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with stats, 28, 0 Note: tail_calls_optimized
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with stats, 32, 0 Note: loads_eliminated
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with stats, 36, 0 Note: stores_eliminated
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with stats, 40, 0 Note: strength_reductions
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with stats, 44, 0 Note: peephole_optimizations

    Return stats
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: build_use_def_chains - Build use-definition chains for all values
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Builds complete use-def and def-use chains for SSA values.
This is fundamental for many optimization passes.
Algorithm:
1. Scan all instructions to find definitions
2. For each definition, create UseDefChain entry
3. Scan instructions to find uses and link to definitions
4. Build reverse def-use chains
@End Reasoning

Process called "build_use_def_chains" that takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks

    Let use_def_chains be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 48
    Let def_use_chains be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 56

    Note: First pass: create entries for all definitions
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
        Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions

        Let j be 0
        While j is less than inst_count:
            Let inst be proc list_get from List with instructions, j
            Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0
            Let result_value be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8

            Note: If instruction produces a result, create use-def chain
            If result_value is not equal to 0:
                Let chain be create_use_def_chain(result_value, opcode, inst, block)
                proc set from Dictionary with use_def_chains, result_value, chain
            End If

            Set j to j plus 1
        End While

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Second pass: record all uses
    Set i to 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Set block to proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Set instructions to proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
        Set inst_count to proc length from List with instructions

        Set j to 0
        While j is less than inst_count:
            Set inst to proc list_get from List with instructions, j
            record_instruction_uses(ctx, inst, block)
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: create_use_def_chain - Create use-def chain for a value
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "create_use_def_chain" that takes value_id as Integer, opcode as Integer, inst as Integer, block as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Allocate UseDefChain structure (64 bytes)
    Let chain be proc allocate from Layout with 64

    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with chain, 0, value_id
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with chain, 4, opcode
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with chain, 8, inst
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with chain, 16, block

    Note: Create uses list
    Let uses be proc list_create from List
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with chain, 24, uses

    Note: Create use_blocks list
    Let use_blocks be proc list_create from List
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with chain, 32, use_blocks

    Note: Initialize use count to 0
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with chain, 40, 0

    Note: Initialize is_constant to 0
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with chain, 44, 0

    Note: Initialize constant_value to 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with chain, 48, 0

    Note: Create reaching definitions set
    Let reaching_defs be proc create from Dictionary
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with chain, 56, reaching_defs

    Return chain
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: record_instruction_uses - Record uses of values in instruction
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "record_instruction_uses" that takes ctx as Integer, inst as Integer, block as Integer returns Integer:
    Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0
    Let use_def_chains be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 48

    Note: Record operand uses based on opcode
    Note: Binary operations use operands at offsets 16 and 24
    If opcode is greater than or equal to 20002 and opcode is less than or equal to 20016:
        Let operand1 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
        Let operand2 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 24

        If operand1 is not equal to 0:
            add_use_to_chain(use_def_chains, operand1, inst, block)
        End If

        If operand2 is not equal to 0:
            add_use_to_chain(use_def_chains, operand2, inst, block)
        End If
    End If

    Note: Comparison operations (20100-20105)
    If opcode is greater than or equal to 20100 and opcode is less than or equal to 20105:
        Set operand1 to proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
        Set operand2 to proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 24

        If operand1 is not equal to 0:
            add_use_to_chain(use_def_chains, operand1, inst, block)
        End If

        If operand2 is not equal to 0:
            add_use_to_chain(use_def_chains, operand2, inst, block)
        End If
    End If

    Note: Memory operations
    If opcode is equal to 20200:  Note: MIR_LOAD
        Let addr be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
        If addr is not equal to 0:
            add_use_to_chain(use_def_chains, addr, inst, block)
        End If
    End If

    If opcode is equal to 20201:  Note: MIR_STORE
        Set addr to proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8
        Let value be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16

        If addr is not equal to 0:
            add_use_to_chain(use_def_chains, addr, inst, block)
        End If

        If value is not equal to 0:
            add_use_to_chain(use_def_chains, value, inst, block)
        End If
    End If

    Note: Return uses value
    If opcode is equal to 20303:  Note: MIR_RETURN
        Set value to proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8
        If value is not equal to 0:
            add_use_to_chain(use_def_chains, value, inst, block)
        End If
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: add_use_to_chain - Add use to value's use-def chain
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "add_use_to_chain" that takes use_def_chains as Integer, value_id as Integer, using_inst as Integer, using_block as Integer returns Integer:
    Let chain be proc get from Dictionary with use_def_chains, value_id

    If chain is equal to 0:
        Note: No definition found for this value (might be parameter or constant)
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Add use to uses list
    Let uses be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with chain, 24
    proc append from List with uses, using_inst

    Note: Add using block to use_blocks
    Let use_blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with chain, 32
    proc append from List with use_blocks, using_block

    Note: Increment use count
    Let use_count be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with chain, 40
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with chain, 40, use_count plus 1

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: optimize_function - Run optimization pipeline on MIR function
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Main entry point for function optimization.
Runs a sequence of optimization passes based on optimization level:
- O0: No optimization
- O1: Basic optimizations (DCE, constant folding, copy propagation)
- O2: Moderate optimizations (O1 + CSE, GVN, simple inlining, Mem2Reg)
- O3: Aggressive optimizations (O2 + loop opts, aggressive inlining, PGO)

Returns 1 if any changes were made, 0 otherwise.
@End Reasoning

Process called "optimize_function" that takes mir_func as Integer, opt_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: No optimization at O0
    If opt_level is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create optimization context
    Let ctx be create_optimization_context(mir_func, opt_level)

    Note: Track if any pass made changes
    Let global_changed be 0

    Note: O1 optimizations
    If opt_level is greater than or equal to 1:
        Note: Dead code elimination
        Let changed be eliminate_dead_code(ctx)
        If changed is equal to 1:
            Set global_changed to 1
        End If

        Note: Constant folding
        Set changed to fold_constants(ctx)
        If changed is equal to 1:
            Set global_changed to 1
        End If

        Note: Constant propagation
        Set changed to propagate_constants(ctx)
        If changed is equal to 1:
            Set global_changed to 1
        End If

        Note: Copy propagation
        Set changed to propagate_copies(ctx)
        If changed is equal to 1:
            Set global_changed to 1
        End If

        Note: Simplify CFG
        Set changed to simplify_cfg(ctx)
        If changed is equal to 1:
            Set global_changed to 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: O2 optimizations
    If opt_level is greater than or equal to 2:
        Note: Common subexpression elimination
        Set changed to eliminate_common_subexpressions(ctx)
        If changed is equal to 1:
            Set global_changed to 1
        End If

        Note: Global value numbering
        Set changed to global_value_numbering(ctx)
        If changed is equal to 1:
            Set global_changed to 1
        End If

        Note: Memory to register promotion
        Set changed to promote_memory_to_registers(ctx)
        If changed is equal to 1:
            Set global_changed to 1
        End If

        Note: Simple function inlining
        Set changed to inline_functions(ctx, 0)  Note: 0 = conservative
        If changed is equal to 1:
            Set global_changed to 1
        End If

        Note: Strength reduction
        Set changed to reduce_strength(ctx)
        If changed is equal to 1:
            Set global_changed to 1
        End If

        Note: Peephole optimizations
        Set changed to apply_peephole_optimizations(ctx)
        If changed is equal to 1:
            Set global_changed to 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: O3 optimizations
    If opt_level is greater than or equal to 3:
        Note: Loop optimizations
        Set changed to optimize_loops(ctx)
        If changed is equal to 1:
            Set global_changed to 1
        End If

        Note: Aggressive function inlining
        Set changed to inline_functions(ctx, 1)  Note: 1 = aggressive
        If changed is equal to 1:
            Set global_changed to 1
        End If

        Note: Tail call optimization
        Set changed to optimize_tail_calls(ctx)
        If changed is equal to 1:
            Set global_changed to 1
        End If

        Note: Profile-guided optimizations
        Let profile_data be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 88
        If profile_data is not equal to 0:
            Set changed to apply_profile_guided_optimizations(ctx)
            If changed is equal to 1:
                Set global_changed to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: Print optimization statistics
    print_optimization_statistics(ctx)

    Return global_changed
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: optimize_program - Program-level (LTO) optimization orchestrator
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
optimize_program is the program-level peer of optimize_function. It is the
single P1-E entry point that compile_program invokes after MIR construction
and before backend lowering. It drives the full LTO pipeline:

Phase A - Whole-program analysis (WPA): build the WPA workspace from the
program-level MIR. WPA records reachability, type hierarchy, escape /
side-effect / purity info, devirtualization candidates (filtered + normalized
per E1), the DCE plan, and cross-bucket priorities.

Phase B - WPA-derived program-level passes (CMO): apply the cross-module
optimizations whose inputs were produced by WPA. At O2 the pipeline runs in
fixed order (inlining -> CP -> DCE, then devirt + specialization + tail-call
+ IPA via apply_all_optimizations). At O3 the pipeline runs in priority order
driven by wpa.optimization_priorities (the bucket-tagged Dict from
compute_optimization_priorities).

Phase C - Per-function passes on the surviving function set. Functions whose
function_id appears in wpa.unreachable_functions are skipped (they will be
removed by sweep_dead_functions in CMO's DCE pass; running optimize_function
on a dead function is wasted work). All surviving functions get the standard
optimize_function pipeline at the requested opt_level.

Phase D - Tear down WPA + CMO workspaces (Tier 3 ownership ends in this
Process's stack frame). The deep-clean destroyer is owned by Layer 1 (WPA)
and Layer 2 (this file modifies cross_module_optimization.runa to add
destroy_cross_module_optimizer).

Opt-level gating (per design v2 section 3.7):
- O0: return 0 immediately. No LTO, no per-function opts. Used for
  fastest-possible compilation.
- O1: per-function only. WPA does not run (its cost is not justified for
  unoptimized builds; per-function passes already give good codegen).
- O2: WPA + CMO fixed-order pipeline + per-function on survivors.
- O3: WPA + CMO priority-driven pipeline + per-function on survivors.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Four-phase pipeline with single failure exits at each allocation boundary.
The WPA pointer is owned by this stack frame (not stored on
OptimizationContext, not global, not on the MIR program). It is passed to
CMO via create_cross_module_optimizer(wpa, mir). The CMO struct stores wpa
at its offset 0 so all CMO passes can read it.

Surviving-function check at Phase C uses Set.contains on
wpa.unreachable_functions (offset 32 of WPA). MIR function records carry
function_id at offset 0 (verified pattern, lines 596 and 1620 of
cross_module_optimization.runa).

optimize_function's contract is "returns 1 if changed, 0 if not, never
fails", so its return value is not inspected for failure. CMO entry points
return non-zero counts on success (their existing contract); we treat them
as best-effort and proceed regardless. The hard-failure cases are: WPA
construction failure, WPA initialization failure, CMO construction failure.

Return value: 0 on success (entire pipeline ran cleanly), 1 on hard error
(WPA or CMO allocation failed). This matches compile_program's expectation
(driver checks for 0 == success).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Called once per source file at LTO time. WPA cost is O(|MIR|) with small
constants - sub-50ms for 10k-function programs (per design section 11.1).
The O2 fixed-order path runs CMO passes in declared order; the O3
priority-driven path adds an O(n log n) sort of the priority Dict (sub-ms
for realistic n=hundreds). Per-function pass cost scales linearly in
|surviving functions|; the unreachable-function skip at Phase C is a
constant-time Set.contains check per function and saves O(|MIR|) work on
dead code.

The WPA workspace adds ~168 bytes of header plus per-candidate storage
(typically O(|MIR| / 100) candidates). The deep-clean destroyer releases
all owned collections in Tier 3 before this Process returns.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
LTO is purely a compile-time transform. No runtime security boundary. The
trust assumption is that WPA's analysis results are sound (reachability is
conservative, devirt candidates are verified, DCE only removes truly dead
code). If WPA over-prunes reachable functions, the resulting binary would
fail at runtime - this is a soundness bug at the WPA level and is gated by
the v0.0.8.5 self-host fixed-point convergence requirement (every commit
must produce bit-identical compiler output across iterations N and N+1).

The priority-driven O3 path applies optimizations in a different order than
O2. Both must produce correct programs; order affects codegen quality, not
semantics. The eight apply_*_candidate wrappers in
cross_module_optimization.runa each delegate to existing CMO machinery
whose security properties are inherited.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "optimize_program" that takes mir as Integer, opt_level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Phase 0 - validate arguments
    If mir is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: O0 fast path - no work at all
    If opt_level is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: O1 - per-function only, no WPA cost
    If opt_level is equal to 1:
        Let functions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with mir, 0
        Let function_count be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with mir, 8
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than function_count:
            Let mir_func be proc list_get from List with functions, i
            If mir_func is not equal to 0:
                optimize_function(mir_func, opt_level)
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Phase A - Whole-program analysis (O2 and O3)
    Let wpa be proc create_whole_program_analysis from WholeProgramAnalysis with mir
    If wpa is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let init_ok be proc initialize_wpa_from_mir from WholeProgramAnalysis with wpa, mir
    If init_ok is equal to 0:
        proc destroy_whole_program_analysis from WholeProgramAnalysis with wpa
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Phase B - WPA-derived CMO passes
    Let cmo be proc create_cross_module_optimizer from CrossModuleOptimization with wpa, mir
    If cmo is equal to 0:
        proc destroy_whole_program_analysis from WholeProgramAnalysis with wpa
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Initialize CMO from WPA (selects inlining candidates, prepares environment)
    proc initialize_cmo_from_wpa from CrossModuleOptimization with cmo

    Note: O2 - fixed-order CMO pipeline
    If opt_level is equal to 2:
        Note: optimize_merged_program: inlining -> CP -> DCE
        proc optimize_merged_program from CrossModuleOptimization with cmo

        Note: apply_all_optimizations: devirt + specialization + tail-call + IPA + verify
        proc apply_all_optimizations from CrossModuleOptimization with cmo
    End If

    Note: O3 - priority-driven CMO pipeline
    If opt_level is greater than or equal to 3:
        proc optimize_merged_program_prioritized from CrossModuleOptimization with cmo
    End If

    Note: Phase C - Per-function intra-function passes on surviving functions
    Let unreachable_set be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with wpa, 32
    Let functions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with mir, 0
    Let function_count be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with mir, 8

    Let fi be 0
    While fi is less than function_count:
        Let mir_func be proc list_get from List with functions, fi
        If mir_func is not equal to 0:
            Let func_id be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with mir_func, 0
            Let is_unreachable be 0
            If unreachable_set is not equal to 0:
                Set is_unreachable to proc contains from Set with unreachable_set, func_id
            End If
            If is_unreachable is equal to 0:
                optimize_function(mir_func, opt_level)
            End If
        End If
        Set fi to fi plus 1
    End While

    Note: Phase D - Tear down (Tier 3 ownership transfer ends here)
    proc destroy_cross_module_optimizer from CrossModuleOptimization with cmo
    proc destroy_whole_program_analysis from WholeProgramAnalysis with wpa

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: eliminate_dead_code - Dead code elimination pass
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Dead code elimination (DCE) removes instructions that don't affect program output.
Algorithm:
1. Mark all instructions as dead initially
2. Mark instructions with side effects as live (stores, calls, returns)
3. Worklist algorithm: mark defining instructions of live instruction operands
4. Sweep: remove all instructions still marked as dead

This is a critical optimization that enables other passes.
@End Reasoning

Process called "eliminate_dead_code" that takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks

    Note: Create worklist of live instructions
    Let worklist be proc list_create from List

    Note: Create set of marked live instructions
    Let live_instructions be proc create from Dictionary

    Note: Mark phase: find initially live instructions
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
        Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions

        Let j be 0
        While j is less than inst_count:
            Let inst be proc list_get from List with instructions, j
            Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0

            Note: Instructions with side effects are always live
            Let is_critical be is_critical_instruction(opcode)
            If is_critical is equal to 1:
                proc set from Dictionary with live_instructions, inst, 1
                proc append from List with worklist, inst
            End If

            Set j to j plus 1
        End While

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Propagate liveness backwards through use-def chains
    Let use_def_chains be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 48

    While proc length from List with worklist is greater than 0:
        Let live_inst be proc list_remove from List with worklist, 0

        Note: Mark all operands' defining instructions as live
        mark_operands_live(live_inst, use_def_chains, live_instructions, worklist)
    End While

    Note: Sweep phase: remove dead instructions
    Let removed_count be 0

    Set i to 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Set block to proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Set instructions to proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
        Set inst_count to proc length from List with instructions

        Note: Iterate backwards to safely remove
        Set j to inst_count minus 1
        While j is greater than or equal to 0:
            Set inst to proc list_get from List with instructions, j
            Let is_live be proc get from Dictionary with live_instructions, inst

            If is_live is equal to 0:
                Note: Instruction is dead, remove it
                proc list_remove from List with instructions, j
                Set removed_count to removed_count plus 1
            End If

            Set j to j minus 1
        End While

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Update statistics
    Let statistics be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 120
    Let current_dce be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with statistics, 0
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with statistics, 0, current_dce plus removed_count

    Note: Return 1 if any instructions were removed
    If removed_count is greater than 0:
        proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with ctx, 80, 1
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: is_critical_instruction - Check if instruction has side effects
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "is_critical_instruction" that takes opcode as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: MIR_STORE (20201) - writes to memory
    If opcode is equal to 20201:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: MIR_RETURN (20303) - affects control flow
    If opcode is equal to 20303:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: MIR_CALL (20304) - may have side effects
    If opcode is equal to 20304:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: MIR_CALL_INDIRECT (20305) - may have side effects
    If opcode is equal to 20305:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: MIR_BRANCH (20301) - affects control flow
    If opcode is equal to 20301:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: MIR_JUMP (20302) - affects control flow
    If opcode is equal to 20302:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: MIR_SWITCH (20306) - affects control flow
    If opcode is equal to 20306:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: mark_operands_live - Mark defining instructions of operands as live
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "mark_operands_live" that takes inst as Integer, use_def_chains as Integer, live_instructions as Integer, worklist as Integer returns Integer:
    Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0

    Note: Get operands based on instruction type
    Note: Binary operations
    If opcode is greater than or equal to 20002 and opcode is less than or equal to 20016:
        Let operand1 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
        Let operand2 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 24

        mark_value_definition_live(operand1, use_def_chains, live_instructions, worklist)
        mark_value_definition_live(operand2, use_def_chains, live_instructions, worklist)
    End If

    Note: Comparison operations
    If opcode is greater than or equal to 20100 and opcode is less than or equal to 20105:
        Set operand1 to proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
        Set operand2 to proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 24

        mark_value_definition_live(operand1, use_def_chains, live_instructions, worklist)
        mark_value_definition_live(operand2, use_def_chains, live_instructions, worklist)
    End If

    Note: LOAD
    If opcode is equal to 20200:
        Let addr be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
        mark_value_definition_live(addr, use_def_chains, live_instructions, worklist)
    End If

    Note: STORE
    If opcode is equal to 20201:
        Set addr to proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8
        Let value be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16

        mark_value_definition_live(addr, use_def_chains, live_instructions, worklist)
        mark_value_definition_live(value, use_def_chains, live_instructions, worklist)
    End If

    Note: RETURN
    If opcode is equal to 20303:
        Set value to proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8
        mark_value_definition_live(value, use_def_chains, live_instructions, worklist)
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: mark_value_definition_live - Mark value's defining instruction as live
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "mark_value_definition_live" that takes value_id as Integer, use_def_chains as Integer, live_instructions as Integer, worklist as Integer returns Integer:
    If value_id is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get use-def chain for this value
    Let chain be proc get from Dictionary with use_def_chains, value_id

    If chain is equal to 0:
        Note: No definition (parameter or constant)
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get defining instruction
    Let defining_inst be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with chain, 8

    Note: Check if already marked live
    Let already_live be proc get from Dictionary with live_instructions, defining_inst

    If already_live is equal to 0:
        Note: Mark as live and add to worklist
        proc set from Dictionary with live_instructions, defining_inst, 1
        proc append from List with worklist, defining_inst
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: fold_constants - Constant folding pass
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Constant folding evaluates expressions with constant operands at compile time.
For example: `x = 2 + 3` becomes `x = 5`

Algorithm:
1. Scan all instructions
2. For instructions with constant operands, evaluate result
3. Replace instruction with constant assignment
4. Update use-def chains

This is a fundamental optimization that often enables other optimizations.
@End Reasoning

Process called "fold_constants" that takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks

    Let constant_values be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 72
    Let folded_count be 0

    Note: Scan all instructions for foldable operations
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
        Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions

        Let j be 0
        While j is less than inst_count:
            Let inst be proc list_get from List with instructions, j
            Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0

            Note: Try to fold this instruction
            Let folded be try_fold_instruction(inst, opcode, constant_values)

            If folded is equal to 1:
                Set folded_count to folded_count plus 1
            End If

            Set j to j plus 1
        End While

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Update statistics
    Let statistics be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 120
    Let current_folded be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with statistics, 4
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with statistics, 4, current_folded plus folded_count

    If folded_count is greater than 0:
        proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with ctx, 80, 1
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: try_fold_instruction - Try to fold constant operation
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "try_fold_instruction" that takes inst as Integer, opcode as Integer, constant_values as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: MIR_CONST - record constant value
    If opcode is equal to 20001:
        Let result_id be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8
        Let const_value be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
        proc set from Dictionary with constant_values, result_id, const_value
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Binary arithmetic operations
    If opcode is greater than or equal to 20002 and opcode is less than or equal to 20006:
        Let operand1_id be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
        Let operand2_id be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 24

        Note: Check if both operands are constants
        Let const1 be proc get from Dictionary with constant_values, operand1_id
        Let const2 be proc get from Dictionary with constant_values, operand2_id

        If const1 is not equal to 0 and const2 is not equal to 0:
            Note: Both operands are constants, fold the operation
            Let result_value be evaluate_binary_operation(opcode, const1, const2)

            Note: Replace instruction with constant
            proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0, 20001 Note: Change to MIR_CONST
            proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with inst, 16, result_value

            Note: Record result as constant
            Set result_id to proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8
            proc set from Dictionary with constant_values, result_id, result_value

            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: evaluate_binary_operation - Evaluate constant binary operation
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "evaluate_binary_operation" that takes opcode as Integer, left as Integer, right as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: MIR_ADD (20002)
    If opcode is equal to 20002:
        Return left plus right
    End If

    Note: MIR_SUB (20003)
    If opcode is equal to 20003:
        Return left minus right
    End If

    Note: MIR_MUL (20004)
    If opcode is equal to 20004:
        Return left multiplied by right
    End If

    Note: MIR_DIV (20005)
    If opcode is equal to 20005:
        If right is equal to 0:
            Return 0  Note: Avoid division by zero
        End If
        Return left divided by right
    End If

    Note: MIR_MOD (20006)
    If opcode is equal to 20006:
        If right is equal to 0:
            Return 0  Note: Avoid division by zero
        End If
        Return left modulo by right
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: propagate_constants - Sparse conditional constant propagation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Sparse Conditional Constant Propagation (SCCP) is a powerful optimization that:
1. Propagates constants through the program
2. Evaluates conditional branches with constant conditions
3. Eliminates unreachable code

Algorithm (Wegman-Zadeck):
1. Initialize all values as UNKNOWN
2. Add entry block to worklist
3. For each instruction in worklist:
   - Evaluate instruction with lattice values
   - If result changes, add uses to worklist
   - Mark reachable edges
4. Replace computable values with constants
5. Remove unreachable code

This is more powerful than simple constant folding as it considers control flow.
@End Reasoning

Process called "propagate_constants" that takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks

    Note: Create lattice value map (0=UNKNOWN, 1=CONSTANT, 2=OVERDEFINED)
    Let lattice_values be proc create from Dictionary

    Note: Create constant value map
    Let const_values be proc create from Dictionary

    Note: Create reachable blocks set
    Let reachable_blocks be proc create from Dictionary

    Note: Create SSA value worklist
    Let ssa_worklist be proc list_create from List

    Note: Create CFG edge worklist
    Let edge_worklist be proc list_create from List

    Note: Add entry block to edge worklist
    Let entry_block be proc list_get from List with blocks, 0
    proc append from List with edge_worklist, entry_block

    Note: Initialize all SSA values to UNKNOWN (0)
    initialize_lattice_values(ctx, lattice_values)

    Note: Main worklist algorithm
    While proc length from List with edge_worklist is greater than 0 or proc length from List with ssa_worklist is greater than 0:
        Note: Process CFG edges
        While proc length from List with edge_worklist is greater than 0:
            Let block be proc list_remove from List with edge_worklist, 0

            Note: Mark block as reachable
            Let already_reachable be proc get from Dictionary with reachable_blocks, block
            If already_reachable is equal to 0:
                proc set from Dictionary with reachable_blocks, block, 1

                Note: Add all instructions to SSA worklist
                Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
                Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions

                Let j be 0
                While j is less than inst_count:
                    Let inst be proc list_get from List with instructions, j
                    proc append from List with ssa_worklist, inst
                    Set j to j plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End While

        Note: Process SSA values
        While proc length from List with ssa_worklist is greater than 0:
            Set inst to proc list_remove from List with ssa_worklist, 0
            evaluate_instruction_sccp(inst, lattice_values, const_values, edge_worklist, ssa_worklist)
        End While
    End While

    Note: Replace constants and remove unreachable code
    Let replaced_count be replace_constants_and_remove_unreachable(ctx, lattice_values, const_values, reachable_blocks)

    Note: Update statistics
    Let statistics be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 120
    Let current_propagated be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with statistics, 8
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with statistics, 8, current_propagated plus replaced_count

    If replaced_count is greater than 0:
        proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with ctx, 80, 1
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: initialize_lattice_values - Initialize SCCP lattice
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "initialize_lattice_values" that takes ctx as Integer, lattice_values as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
        Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions

        Let j be 0
        While j is less than inst_count:
            Let inst be proc list_get from List with instructions, j
            Let result_id be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8

            If result_id is not equal to 0:
                proc set from Dictionary with lattice_values, result_id, 0 Note: UNKNOWN
            End If

            Set j to j plus 1
        End While

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: evaluate_instruction_sccp - Evaluate instruction for SCCP
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "evaluate_instruction_sccp" that takes inst as Integer, lattice_values as Integer, const_values as Integer, edge_worklist as Integer, ssa_worklist as Integer returns Integer:
    Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0
    Let result_id be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8

    Note: MIR_CONST - constant value
    If opcode is equal to 20001:
        Let const_value be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
        proc set from Dictionary with lattice_values, result_id, 1 Note: CONSTANT
        proc set from Dictionary with const_values, result_id, const_value
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Binary operations
    If opcode is greater than or equal to 20002 and opcode is less than or equal to 20006:
        Let operand1_id be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
        Let operand2_id be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 24

        Let lattice1 be proc get from Dictionary with lattice_values, operand1_id
        Let lattice2 be proc get from Dictionary with lattice_values, operand2_id

        Note: If either operand is OVERDEFINED (2), result is OVERDEFINED
        If lattice1 is equal to 2 or lattice2 is equal to 2:
            proc set from Dictionary with lattice_values, result_id, 2 Note: OVERDEFINED
            Return 1
        End If

        Note: If both operands are CONSTANT (1), compute result
        If lattice1 is equal to 1 and lattice2 is equal to 1:
            Let const1 be proc get from Dictionary with const_values, operand1_id
            Let const2 be proc get from Dictionary with const_values, operand2_id
            Let result_value be evaluate_binary_operation(opcode, const1, const2)

            proc set from Dictionary with lattice_values, result_id, 1 Note: CONSTANT
            proc set from Dictionary with const_values, result_id, result_value
            Return 1
        End If

        Note: Otherwise result remains UNKNOWN (0)
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: For other instructions, conservatively mark as OVERDEFINED
    proc set from Dictionary with lattice_values, result_id, 2

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: replace_constants_and_remove_unreachable - Apply SCCP results
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "replace_constants_and_remove_unreachable" that takes ctx as Integer, lattice_values as Integer, const_values as Integer, reachable_blocks as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks

    Let replaced_count be 0

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let is_reachable be proc get from Dictionary with reachable_blocks, block

        Note: Remove unreachable blocks
        If is_reachable is equal to 0:
            Note: Block is unreachable, remove it
            proc list_remove from List with blocks, i
            Set block_count to block_count minus 1
            Set i to i minus 1
            Set replaced_count to replaced_count plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Note: Replace constant values in reachable blocks
            Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
            Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions

            Let j be 0
            While j is less than inst_count:
                Let inst be proc list_get from List with instructions, j
                Let result_id be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8

                Let lattice be proc get from Dictionary with lattice_values, result_id

                Note: If result is constant, replace instruction
                If lattice is equal to 1:
                    Let const_value be proc get from Dictionary with const_values, result_id

                    Note: Replace with MIR_CONST
                    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0, 20001
                    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with inst, 16, const_value

                    Set replaced_count to replaced_count plus 1
                End If

                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return replaced_count
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: propagate_copies - Copy propagation pass
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Copy propagation replaces uses of copy destinations with copy sources.
For example: `x = y; z = x + 1` becomes `z = y + 1` and `x = y` can be eliminated.

This simplifies the program and enables other optimizations.
@End Reasoning

Process called "propagate_copies" that takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks

    Let use_def_chains be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 48
    Let propagated_count be 0

    Note: Find all copy instructions
    Let copy_map be proc create from Dictionary

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
        Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions

        Let j be 0
        While j is less than inst_count:
            Let inst be proc list_get from List with instructions, j
            Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0

            Note: Detect copy instructions (MOV, COPY, identity assignments)
            Note: Opcode 100 = MOV (move/copy instruction)
            Note: Opcode 101 = IDENTITY (no-op transformation)
            Note: Opcode 102 = PHI with single operand (copy in SSA form)

            If opcode is equal to 100:  Note: MOV instruction
                Note: result = source (no transformation)
                Let result_value be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8 Note: Destination register
                Let source_value be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16 Note: Source register

                Note: Record copy relationship: result_value = source_value
                proc set from Dictionary with copy_map, result_value, source_value
            End If

            If opcode is equal to 101:  Note: IDENTITY instruction
                Set result_value to proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8
                Set source_value to proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
                proc set from Dictionary with copy_map, result_value, source_value
            End If

            If opcode is equal to 102:  Note: PHI instruction
                Note: Check if PHI has single operand (degenerate PHI = copy)
                Let operand_count be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 20
                If operand_count is equal to 1:
                    Set result_value to proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8
                    Set source_value to proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
                    proc set from Dictionary with copy_map, result_value, source_value
                End If
            End If

            Set j to j plus 1
        End While

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Propagate copies through use-def chains
    Let copy_keys be proc keys from Dictionary with copy_map
    Let copy_count be proc length from List with copy_keys

    Let k be 0
    While k is less than copy_count:
        Let dest_value be proc list_get from List with copy_keys, k
        Set source_value to proc get from Dictionary with copy_map, dest_value

        Note: Get use-def chain for destination
        Let chain be proc get from Dictionary with use_def_chains, dest_value
        If chain is not equal to 0:
            Let uses be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with chain, 24
            Let use_count be proc length from List with uses

            Note: Replace all uses of dest with source
            Let u be 0
            While u is less than use_count:
                Let using_inst be proc list_get from List with uses, u
                replace_value_in_instruction(using_inst, dest_value, source_value)
                Set propagated_count to propagated_count plus 1
                Set u to u plus 1
            End While
        End If

        Set k to k plus 1
    End While

    Note: Update statistics
    Let statistics be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 120
    Let current_copies be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with statistics, 12
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with statistics, 12, current_copies plus propagated_count

    If propagated_count is greater than 0:
        proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with ctx, 80, 1
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: replace_value_in_instruction - Replace value ID in instruction operands
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "replace_value_in_instruction" that takes inst as Integer, old_value as Integer, new_value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check operand slots and replace if matching
    Let operand1 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
    If operand1 is equal to old_value:
        proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16, new_value
    End If

    Let operand2 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 24
    If operand2 is equal to old_value:
        proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 24, new_value
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: eliminate_common_subexpressions - CSE pass
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Common Subexpression Elimination (CSE) identifies redundant computations and
reuses previously computed values.

For example: `x = a + b; y = a + b` becomes `x = a + b; y = x`

This uses value numbering to identify equivalent expressions.
@End Reasoning

Process called "eliminate_common_subexpressions" that takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks

    Let value_numbers be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 64
    Let eliminated_count be 0

    Note: For each block, perform local CSE
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
        Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions

        Note: Map expression signatures to their result values
        Let expression_map be proc create from Dictionary

        Let j be 0
        While j is less than inst_count:
            Let inst be proc list_get from List with instructions, j
            Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0
            Let result_id be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8

            Note: Compute expression signature
            Let signature be compute_expression_signature(inst, opcode)

            If signature is not equal to 0:
                Note: Check if we've seen this expression before
                Let previous_result be proc get from Dictionary with expression_map, signature

                If previous_result is not equal to 0:
                    Note: Redundant computation found, replace uses
                    replace_all_uses(ctx, result_id, previous_result)
                    Set eliminated_count to eliminated_count plus 1

                    Note: Mark instruction for deletion
                    Let dead_instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 104
                    proc set from Dictionary with dead_instructions, inst, 1
                Otherwise:
                    Note: Record this expression
                    proc set from Dictionary with expression_map, signature, result_id
                End If
            End If

            Set j to j plus 1
        End While

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Remove eliminated instructions
    remove_dead_instructions(ctx)

    Note: Update statistics
    Let statistics be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 120
    Let current_cse be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with statistics, 16
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with statistics, 16, current_cse plus eliminated_count

    If eliminated_count is greater than 0:
        proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with ctx, 80, 1
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: compute_expression_signature - Compute hash for expression
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "compute_expression_signature" that takes inst as Integer, opcode as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Only pure operations can be CSE'd
    If is_pure_operation(opcode) is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Compute signature: opcode * 1000000 + operand1 * 1000 + operand2
    Let operand1 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
    Let operand2 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 24

    Let signature be opcode multiplied by 1000000 plus operand1 multiplied by 1000 plus operand2

    Return signature
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: is_pure_operation - Check if operation is side-effect free
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "is_pure_operation" that takes opcode as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Arithmetic operations (20002-20016)
    If opcode is greater than or equal to 20002 and opcode is less than or equal to 20016:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Comparison operations (20100-20105)
    If opcode is greater than or equal to 20100 and opcode is less than or equal to 20105:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: CAST (20400)
    If opcode is equal to 20400:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: replace_all_uses - Replace all uses of a value
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "replace_all_uses" that takes ctx as Integer, old_value as Integer, new_value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let use_def_chains be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 48
    Let chain be proc get from Dictionary with use_def_chains, old_value

    If chain is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let uses be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with chain, 24
    Let use_count be proc length from List with uses

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than use_count:
        Let using_inst be proc list_get from List with uses, i
        replace_value_in_instruction(using_inst, old_value, new_value)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return use_count
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: remove_dead_instructions - Remove instructions marked for deletion
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "remove_dead_instructions" that takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks

    Let dead_instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 104

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
        Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions

        Note: Remove backwards to avoid index issues
        Let j be inst_count minus 1
        While j is greater than or equal to 0:
            Let inst be proc list_get from List with instructions, j
            Let is_dead be proc get from Dictionary with dead_instructions, inst

            If is_dead is equal to 1:
                proc list_remove from List with instructions, j
            End If

            Set j to j minus 1
        End While

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Clear dead instructions set
    Let keys be proc keys from Dictionary with dead_instructions
    Let key_count be proc length from List with keys

    Let k be 0
    While k is less than key_count:
        Let key be proc list_get from List with keys, k
        proc remove from Dictionary with dead_instructions, key
        Set k to k plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: global_value_numbering - GVN pass
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Global Value Numbering (GVN) is a more powerful version of CSE that works
across basic blocks. It assigns value numbers to expressions and identifies
equivalent expressions program-wide.

This is more powerful than local CSE and can eliminate redundancies across
control flow joins.
@End Reasoning

Process called "global_value_numbering" that takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Proper GVN with dominator tree traversal and scoped hash tables
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks

    Note: Build dominator tree for the CFG
    Let dom_tree be build_dominator_tree(ctx)

    Note: Create scoped value numbering table (stack of hash tables)
    Let vn_stack be proc list_create from List
    Let eliminated_count be 0

    Note: Traverse CFG in dominator tree preorder
    Let entry_block be proc list_get from List with blocks, 0
    Set eliminated_count to gvn_traverse_block(ctx, entry_block, dom_tree, vn_stack, 0)

    Note: Cleanup dominator tree
    destroy_dominator_tree(dom_tree)

    Return eliminated_count
End Process

@Reasoning
Builds a dominator tree for the control flow graph. The dominator tree
represents the dominance relationship: block A dominates block B if all
paths to B go through A.

Uses the Lengauer-Tarjan algorithm for O(n log n) dominator tree construction.
@End Reasoning

Process called "build_dominator_tree" that takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks

    Note: Create dominator tree structure
    Let dom_tree be proc allocate from Layout with 64

    Note: Create immediate dominator map (idom)
    Let idom be proc create from Dictionary
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with dom_tree, 0, idom

    Note: Create dominated children map
    Let children be proc create from Dictionary
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with dom_tree, 8, children

    Note: Entry block dominates itself
    Let entry_block be proc list_get from List with blocks, 0
    proc set from Dictionary with idom, entry_block, entry_block

    Note: Initialize all other blocks to have no immediate dominator
    Let i be 1
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        proc set from Dictionary with idom, block, 0
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Compute dominators using iterative dataflow
    Let changed be 1
    While changed is equal to 1:
        Set changed to 0

        Set i to 1  Note: Skip entry block
        While i is less than block_count:
            Set block to proc list_get from List with blocks, i

            Note: Get predecessors of this block
            Let preds be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 16
            Let pred_count be proc length from List with preds

            Note: Find new immediate dominator (intersection of predecessor dominators)
            Let new_idom be 0
            Let p be 0
            While p is less than pred_count:
                Let pred be proc list_get from List with preds, p
                Let pred_idom be proc get from Dictionary with idom, pred

                If pred_idom is not equal to 0:
                    If new_idom is equal to 0:
                        Set new_idom to pred
                    Otherwise:
                        Set new_idom to intersect_dominators(idom, new_idom, pred)
                    End If
                End If

                Set p to p plus 1
            End While

            Note: Check if immediate dominator changed
            Let old_idom be proc get from Dictionary with idom, block
            If new_idom is not equal to old_idom:
                proc set from Dictionary with idom, block, new_idom
                Set changed to 1
            End If

            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End While

    Note: Build children map from idom
    Set i to 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Set block to proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let block_idom be proc get from Dictionary with idom, block

        If block_idom is not equal to 0:
            If block_idom is not equal to block:  Note: Skip entry block self-loop
                Note: Add block as child of its immediate dominator
                Let child_list be proc get from Dictionary with children, block_idom
                If child_list is equal to 0:
                    Set child_list to proc list_create from List
                    proc set from Dictionary with children, block_idom, child_list
                End If
                proc append from List with child_list, block
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return dom_tree
End Process

@Reasoning
Finds the common dominator of two blocks by walking up the dominator tree.
@End Reasoning

Process called "intersect_dominators" that takes idom as Integer, b1 as Integer, b2 as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Walk up dominator tree from both blocks until they meet
    Let finger1 be b1
    Let finger2 be b2

    While finger1 is not equal to finger2:
        Note: Move finger that's "lower" in the tree up
        If finger1 is less than finger2:
            Set finger1 to proc get from Dictionary with idom, finger1
        Otherwise:
            Set finger2 to proc get from Dictionary with idom, finger2
        End If

        Note: Guard against infinite loop (shouldn't happen with valid CFG)
        If finger1 is equal to 0:
            Return finger2
        End If
        If finger2 is equal to 0:
            Return finger1
        End If
    End While

    Return finger1
End Process

@Reasoning
Traverses the dominator tree in preorder, performing value numbering on each block.
Uses scoped hash tables to maintain value numbers - when entering a block, push
a new scope; when leaving, pop it.
@End Reasoning

Process called "gvn_traverse_block" that takes ctx as Integer, block as Integer, dom_tree as Integer, vn_stack as Integer, eliminated as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Push new value numbering scope for this block
    Let vn_table be proc create from Dictionary
    proc append from List with vn_stack, vn_table

    Note: Process instructions in this block
    Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
    Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions

    Let j be 0
    While j is less than inst_count:
        Let inst be proc list_get from List with instructions, j
        Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0

        Note: Skip non-expression instructions
        If opcode is greater than or equal to 20000:  Note: MIR instructions
            If opcode is less than 21000:  Note: Expression range
                Note: Compute expression hash
                Let expr_hash be hash_instruction(inst)

                Note: Look up in scoped hash tables (search from innermost to outermost)
                Let existing_value be lookup_value_number(vn_stack, expr_hash)

                If existing_value is not equal to 0:
                    Note: Found equivalent expression - replace with existing value
                    Let result be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8
                    replace_all_uses(ctx, result, existing_value)

                    Note: Mark instruction as dead
                    Let dead_instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 104
                    proc set from Dictionary with dead_instructions, inst, 1

                    Let eliminated be eliminated plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    Note: New expression - assign value number
                    Set result to proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8
                    proc set from Dictionary with vn_table, expr_hash, result
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set j to j plus 1
    End While

    Note: Recursively traverse dominated children
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with dom_tree, 8
    Let child_list be proc get from Dictionary with children, block

    If child_list is not equal to 0:
        Let child_count be proc length from List with child_list
        Let c be 0
        While c is less than child_count:
            Let child_block be proc list_get from List with child_list, c
            Set eliminated to gvn_traverse_block(ctx, child_block, dom_tree, vn_stack, eliminated)
            Set c to c plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: Pop value numbering scope when leaving block
    proc list_remove from List with vn_stack, List.length(vn_stack minus 1)

    Return eliminated
End Process

@Reasoning
Hashes an instruction to create a unique identifier for the expression.
Two instructions that compute the same value will hash to the same value.
@End Reasoning

Process called "hash_instruction" that takes inst as Integer returns Integer:
    Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0
    Let hash be opcode multiplied by 31

    Note: Hash operands
    Let operand1 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
    Let operand2 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 20

    Set hash to hash plus (operand1 multiplied by 17)
    Set hash to hash plus (operand2 multiplied by 13)

    Return hash
End Process

@Reasoning
Looks up a value number in the scoped hash table stack.
Searches from innermost scope to outermost.
@End Reasoning

Process called "lookup_value_number" that takes vn_stack as Integer, expr_hash as Integer returns Integer:
    Let stack_size be proc length from List with vn_stack
    Let i be stack_size minus 1

    While i is greater than or equal to 0:
        Let vn_table be proc list_get from List with vn_stack, i
        Let value be proc get from Dictionary with vn_table, expr_hash

        If value is not equal to 0:
            Return value
        End If

        Set i to i minus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Destroys the dominator tree and frees associated resources.
@End Reasoning

Process called "destroy_dominator_tree" that takes dom_tree as Integer returns Integer:
    Let idom be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with dom_tree, 0
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with dom_tree, 8

    proc destroy from Dictionary with idom

    Note: Destroy all children lists
    Let child_keys be proc keys from Dictionary with children
    Let key_count be proc length from List with child_keys

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than key_count:
        Let key be proc list_get from List with child_keys, i
        Let child_list be proc get from Dictionary with children, key
        proc list_destroy from List with child_list
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc destroy from Dictionary with children
    proc deallocate from Layout with dom_tree

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: promote_memory_to_registers - Mem2Reg pass
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Memory-to-Register promotion (Mem2Reg) converts memory operations on
stack-allocated variables to SSA register values.

For example:
  alloca %x
  store 5, %x
  %1 = load %x

Becomes:
  %x = 5

This is crucial for enabling other optimizations and reducing memory traffic.

Algorithm:
1. Identify promotable allocas (single allocation, no address taken)
2. Remove loads/stores to promotable allocas
3. Insert phi nodes at merge points
4. Convert to SSA form

This pass is already partially done during SSA construction, so this is
primarily cleanup and validation.
@End Reasoning

Process called "promote_memory_to_registers" that takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks

    Let promoted_count be 0

    Note: Find promotable allocas
    Let promotable_allocas be proc create from Dictionary

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
        Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions

        Let j be 0
        While j is less than inst_count:
            Let inst be proc list_get from List with instructions, j
            Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0

            Note: MIR_ALLOCA (20202)
            If opcode is equal to 20202:
                Let alloca_id be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8

                Note: Check if promotable (no address taken)
                Let is_promotable be check_promotable_alloca(ctx, alloca_id)

                If is_promotable is equal to 1:
                    proc set from Dictionary with promotable_allocas, alloca_id, 1
                End If
            End If

            Set j to j plus 1
        End While

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Eliminate loads/stores to promotable allocas
    Set i to 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Set block to proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Set instructions to proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
        Set inst_count to proc length from List with instructions

        Set j to inst_count minus 1
        While j is greater than or equal to 0:
            Set inst to proc list_get from List with instructions, j
            Set opcode to proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0

            Note: MIR_LOAD from promotable alloca
            If opcode is equal to 20200:
                Let addr be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
                Set is_promotable to proc get from Dictionary with promotable_allocas, addr

                If is_promotable is equal to 1:
                    Note: This load should have been eliminated during SSA construction
                    Note: Remove it now
                    proc list_remove from List with instructions, j
                    Set promoted_count to promoted_count plus 1
                End If
            End If

            Note: MIR_STORE to promotable alloca
            If opcode is equal to 20201:
                Set addr to proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8
                Set is_promotable to proc get from Dictionary with promotable_allocas, addr

                If is_promotable is equal to 1:
                    Note: This store should have been eliminated during SSA construction
                    Note: Remove it now
                    proc list_remove from List with instructions, j
                    Set promoted_count to promoted_count plus 1
                End If
            End If

            Set j to j minus 1
        End While

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Update statistics
    Let statistics be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 120
    Let current_loads be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with statistics, 32
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with statistics, 32, current_loads plus promoted_count

    If promoted_count is greater than 0:
        proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with ctx, 80, 1
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: check_promotable_alloca - Check if alloca can be promoted
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "check_promotable_alloca" that takes ctx as Integer, alloca_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Let use_def_chains be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 48
    Let chain be proc get from Dictionary with use_def_chains, alloca_id

    If chain is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let uses be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with chain, 24
    Let use_count be proc length from List with uses

    Note: Check that all uses are loads or stores (no address taken)
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than use_count:
        Let using_inst be proc list_get from List with uses, i
        Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with using_inst, 0

        Note: Only LOAD and STORE are allowed
        If opcode is not equal to 20200 and opcode is not equal to 20201:
            Return 0  Note: Address is taken or used in other way
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Remaining optimization pass stubs
Note: These implement additional optimization passes for completeness
Note: ============================================================================

@Implementation
CFG simplification performs structural optimizations on the control flow graph:
1. Merge basic blocks when predecessor has single successor and successor has single predecessor
2. Remove empty blocks (blocks with only a jump instruction)
3. Eliminate unreachable blocks
4. Thread jumps (if block A jumps to B and B immediately jumps to C, A jumps directly to C)
5. Hoist common instructions from conditional branches

This reduces CFG complexity and enables further optimizations.
@End Implementation

Process called "simplify_cfg" that takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks
    Let changed be 0

    Note: Pass 1: Merge blocks with single predecessor/successor
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let successors be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 24
        Let succ_count be proc length from List with successors

        Note: Check if block has exactly one successor
        If succ_count is equal to 1:
            Let successor be proc list_get from List with successors, 0
            Let pred_list be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with successor, 16
            Let pred_count be proc length from List with pred_list

            Note: Check if successor has exactly one predecessor (this block)
            If pred_count is equal to 1:
                Note: Merge: move successor's instructions into this block
                Let block_insts be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
                Let succ_insts be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with successor, 8
                Let succ_inst_count be proc length from List with succ_insts

                Note: Remove jump from block (last instruction)
                Let block_inst_count be proc length from List with block_insts
                If block_inst_count is greater than 0:
                    proc list_remove from List with block_insts, block_inst_count minus 1
                End If

                Note: Append successor instructions to block
                Let si be 0
                While si is less than succ_inst_count:
                    Let inst be proc list_get from List with succ_insts, si
                    proc append from List with block_insts, inst
                    Set si to (si plus 1)
                End While

                Note: Update block's successors to successor's successors
                Let succ_successors be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with successor, 24
                proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 24, succ_successors

                Note: Mark successor for removal
                proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with successor, 0, 0 Note: Mark as dead
                Set changed to 1
            End If
        End If

        Set i to (i plus 1)
    End While

    Note: Pass 2: Remove empty blocks (only contain jump)
    Set i to 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Set block to proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
        Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions

        Note: Check if block only has a jump instruction
        If inst_count is equal to 1:
            Set inst to proc list_get from List with instructions, 0
            Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0

            Note: MIR_JUMP is 20302
            If opcode is equal to 20302:
                Note: Thread predecessors to jump directly to successor
                Let target be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with inst, 8
                Let predecessors be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 16
                Set pred_count to proc length from List with predecessors

                Let pi be 0
                While pi is less than pred_count:
                    Let pred be proc list_get from List with predecessors, pi
                    Note: Update pred's successors: replace block with target
                    Let pred_succs be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with pred, 24
                    Let ps_count be proc length from List with pred_succs

                    Let psi be 0
                    While psi is less than ps_count:
                        Let succ be proc list_get from List with pred_succs, psi
                        If succ is equal to block:
                            proc list_set from List with pred_succs, psi, target
                        End If
                        Set psi to (psi plus 1)
                    End While

                    Note: Update terminator instruction in predecessor
                    Let pred_insts be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with pred, 8
                    Let pred_inst_count be proc length from List with pred_insts
                    If pred_inst_count is greater than 0:
                        Let term_inst be proc list_get from List with pred_insts, pred_inst_count minus 1
                        Let term_opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with term_inst, 0

                        Note: Update branch/jump target
                        If term_opcode is equal to 20301:  Note: MIR_BRANCH
                            Let then_block be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with term_inst, 16
                            Let else_block be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with term_inst, 24
                            If then_block is equal to block:
                                proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with term_inst, 16, target
                            End If
                            If else_block is equal to block:
                                proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with term_inst, 24, target
                            End If
                        Otherwise:
                            If term_opcode is equal to 20302:  Note: MIR_JUMP
                                proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with term_inst, 8, target
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If

                    Set pi to (pi plus 1)
                End While

                Note: Mark empty block for removal
                proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with block, 0, 0
                Set changed to 1
            End If
        End If

        Set i to (i plus 1)
    End While

    Note: Pass 3: Remove dead blocks from CFG
    Let new_blocks be proc list_create from List
    Set i to 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Set block to proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let block_id be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with block, 0
        If block_id is not equal to 0:  Note: Not marked as dead
            proc append from List with new_blocks, block
        End If
        Set i to (i plus 1)
    End While

    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0, new_blocks

    Note: Update changed flag in context
    If changed is equal to 1:
        proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with ctx, 80, 1
    End If

    Return changed
End Process

@Implementation
Loop optimization identifies loops in the CFG and applies:
1. Loop-Invariant Code Motion (LICM) - hoist invariant computations out of loops
2. Loop Unrolling - replicate loop body to reduce overhead
3. Loop Vectorization - convert scalar operations to SIMD operations
4. Strength Reduction - replace expensive operations with cheaper equivalents in loops

This requires:
- Loop detection (natural loops via back edges)
- Dominance analysis
- Dataflow analysis to identify invariants
- Dependency analysis for vectorization
@End Implementation

@Reasoning
The loop and inlining workers below operate on this module's register-based
instruction model: 64-byte instruction records with the opcode as an int32
at offset 0, the destination register as an int32 at offset 8, operand
registers as int32 at offsets 16 and 24 (except CONST, which stores its
immediate as an int64 at offset 16, and BRANCH/JUMP, which store target
block pointers as int64 at offsets 16/24 and 8 respectively); blocks keep
their predecessor block-pointer List at offset 16, their successor
block-pointer List at offset 24, and their instruction List at offset 8.
These are the exact conventions used by the surrounding passes in this
file (try_fold_instruction, eliminate_empty_blocks, optimize_tail_calls).

Soundness rules:
- An instruction is loop-invariant when it is pure compute (CONST,
  add/sub/mul and the bitwise band 20002-20016 excluding DIV/MOD whose
  divisor is not a proven non-zero constant, or a comparison
  20100-20105), its destination register has exactly one definition in
  the loop, and its operand registers have no definition inside the loop.
  It may be hoisted only into a unique out-of-loop predecessor of the
  header (the preheader), which dominates every loop iteration.
- A loop is fully unrollable when it is a single-block self-loop whose
  induction variable, init, step, and bound are all proven constants and
  whose comparison result feeds only the loop branch; replicating the
  straight-line body trip-count times and replacing the branch with an
  unconditional jump to the exit is then semantically exact.
- A callee is inlinable at the trivial tier when its body is one block of
  locally-defined pure compute ending in RETURN: such a function is a
  compile-time constant function, so the call site is replaced in place
  with a CONST of the evaluated result. No register renaming is required
  because no callee instruction survives into the caller.
@End Reasoning

Process called "hoist_loop_invariants" that takes ctx as Integer, loop_info as Integer returns Integer:
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If loop_info is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let header be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with loop_info, 0
    Let body_blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with loop_info, 16
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If body_blocks is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let body_count be proc length from List with body_blocks

    Note: Locate the unique out-of-loop predecessor of the header (the
    Note: preheader). Multiple outside entries mean there is no single
    Note: dominating insertion point, so hoisting is skipped entirely.
    Let header_preds be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with header, 16
    If header_preds is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let preheader be 0
    Let outside_count be 0
    Let hp be 0
    Let hp_count be proc length from List with header_preds
    While hp is less than hp_count:
        Let pred be proc list_get from List with header_preds, hp
        Let in_body be 0
        Let bi be 0
        While bi is less than body_count:
            Let bb be proc list_get from List with body_blocks, bi
            If bb is equal to pred:
                Set in_body to 1
                Set bi to body_count
            End If
            Set bi to (bi plus 1)
        End While
        If in_body is equal to 0:
            Set preheader to pred
            Set outside_count to (outside_count plus 1)
        End If
        Set hp to (hp plus 1)
    End While

    If outside_count is not equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If preheader is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let constant_values be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 72
    Let total_moved be 0
    Let changed be 1

    While changed is equal to 1:
        Set changed to 0

        Note: Collect every register defined in the loop and how many
        Note: times it is defined (a multiply-defined register is never
        Note: safe to hoist in a register model)
        Let loop_defs be proc create from Dictionary

        Let cb be 0
        While cb is less than body_count:
            Let body_block be proc list_get from List with body_blocks, cb
            Let body_insts be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with body_block, 8
            Let body_inst_count be proc length from List with body_insts
            Let ci be 0
            While ci is less than body_inst_count:
                Let cinst be proc list_get from List with body_insts, ci
                Let cresult be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with cinst, 8
                If cresult is not equal to 0:
                    Let def_count be proc get from Dictionary with loop_defs, cresult
                    proc set from Dictionary with loop_defs, cresult, def_count plus 1
                End If
                Set ci to (ci plus 1)
            End While
            Set cb to (cb plus 1)
        End While

        Note: Scan for an invariant instruction and hoist it
        Set cb to 0
        While cb is less than body_count:
            Let body_block be proc list_get from List with body_blocks, cb
            Let body_insts be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with body_block, 8
            Let body_inst_count be proc length from List with body_insts

            Let ci be 0
            While ci is less than body_inst_count:
                Let cinst be proc list_get from List with body_insts, ci
                Let copcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with cinst, 0
                Let is_candidate be 0

                Note: CONST is always invariant
                If copcode is equal to 20001:
                    Set is_candidate to 1
                End If

                Note: Arithmetic / bitwise band, excluding DIV (20005) and
                Note: MOD (20006) unless the divisor is a proven non-zero
                Note: constant (hoisting may execute a conditionally
                Note: guarded division unconditionally)
                If copcode is greater than or equal to 20002:
                    If copcode is less than or equal to 20016:
                        Set is_candidate to 1
                        If copcode is equal to 20005 or copcode is equal to 20006:
                            Set is_candidate to 0
                            If constant_values is not equal to 0:
                                Let divisor_reg be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with cinst, 24
                                Let divisor_const be proc get from Dictionary with constant_values, divisor_reg
                                If divisor_const is not equal to 0:
                                    Set is_candidate to 1
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If

                Note: Comparisons are pure compute
                If copcode is greater than or equal to 20100:
                    If copcode is less than or equal to 20105:
                        Set is_candidate to 1
                    End If
                End If

                If is_candidate is equal to 1:
                    Let cresult be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with cinst, 8
                    If cresult is equal to 0:
                        Set is_candidate to 0
                    Otherwise:
                        Let own_defs be proc get from Dictionary with loop_defs, cresult
                        If own_defs is not equal to 1:
                            Set is_candidate to 0
                        End If
                    End If
                End If

                Note: Operands must have no definition inside the loop
                Note: (CONST carries an immediate, not operand registers)
                If is_candidate is equal to 1:
                    If copcode is not equal to 20001:
                        Let cop1 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with cinst, 16
                        Let cop2 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with cinst, 24
                        If cop1 is not equal to 0:
                            Let op1_defs be proc get from Dictionary with loop_defs, cop1
                            If op1_defs is not equal to 0:
                                Set is_candidate to 0
                            End If
                        End If
                        If cop2 is not equal to 0:
                            Let op2_defs be proc get from Dictionary with loop_defs, cop2
                            If op2_defs is not equal to 0:
                                Set is_candidate to 0
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If

                If is_candidate is equal to 1:
                    Note: Hoist: remove from the loop block and insert into
                    Note: the preheader before its terminator
                    proc list_remove from List with body_insts, ci

                    Let pre_insts be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with preheader, 8
                    Let pre_count be proc length from List with pre_insts
                    Let insert_pos be pre_count
                    If pre_count is greater than 0:
                        Let pre_last be proc list_get from List with pre_insts, pre_count minus 1
                        Let pre_last_opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with pre_last, 0
                        Let is_terminator be 0
                        If pre_last_opcode is equal to 20301:
                            Set is_terminator to 1
                        End If
                        If pre_last_opcode is equal to 20302:
                            Set is_terminator to 1
                        End If
                        If pre_last_opcode is equal to 20303:
                            Set is_terminator to 1
                        End If
                        If pre_last_opcode is equal to 20306:
                            Set is_terminator to 1
                        End If
                        If is_terminator is equal to 1:
                            Set insert_pos to pre_count minus 1
                        End If
                    End If
                    proc list_insert from List with pre_insts, insert_pos, cinst

                    Set total_moved to (total_moved plus 1)
                    Set changed to 1
                    Note: Restart the fixpoint scan with fresh definition
                    Note: counts
                    Set ci to body_inst_count
                    Set cb to body_count
                Otherwise:
                    Set ci to (ci plus 1)
                End If
            End While

            Set cb to (cb plus 1)
        End While

        proc destroy from Dictionary with loop_defs
    End While

    Return total_moved
End Process

Process called "analyze_loop_unroll_opportunity" that takes ctx as Integer, loop_info as Integer returns Integer:
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    If loop_info is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let header be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with loop_info, 0
    Let latch be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with loop_info, 8
    Let body_blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with loop_info, 16

    Note: Only single-block self-loops are analyzed: the unroll transform
    Note: replicates straight-line code, which is exact only when the
    Note: entire iteration is one block
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    If header is not equal to latch:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let body_count be proc length from List with body_blocks
    If body_count is not equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let insts be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with header, 8
    Let inst_count be proc length from List with insts
    If inst_count is less than 3:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: The block must end with comparison + conditional branch
    Let branch be proc list_get from List with insts, inst_count minus 1
    Let branch_opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with branch, 0
    If branch_opcode is not equal to 20301:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let cmp be proc list_get from List with insts, inst_count minus 2
    Let cmp_opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with cmp, 0
    If cmp_opcode is less than 20100:
        Return 1
    End If
    If cmp_opcode is greater than 20105:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: The branch condition must be exactly the comparison result
    Let cmp_result be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with cmp, 8
    Let branch_cond be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with branch, 8
    If cmp_result is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    If branch_cond is not equal to cmp_result:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: The loop must continue on the TRUE edge (then-target is the
    Note: header) so trip count counts iterations while the comparison
    Note: holds
    Let then_block be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with branch, 16
    If then_block is not equal to header:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: The comparison result must feed only the branch
    Let use_scan be 0
    While use_scan is less than inst_count minus 1:
        Let uinst be proc list_get from List with insts, use_scan
        Let uop1 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with uinst, 16
        Let uop2 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with uinst, 24
        Let uopcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with uinst, 0
        If uopcode is not equal to 20001:
            If uop1 is equal to cmp_result:
                Return 1
            End If
            If uop2 is equal to cmp_result:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
        Set use_scan to (use_scan plus 1)
    End While

    Note: Induction variable: comparison operand1; bound: operand2
    Let iv_reg be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with cmp, 16
    Let bound_reg be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with cmp, 24
    If iv_reg is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Step: a single ADD in the body with result == iv and
    Note: operand1 == iv and a constant operand2
    Let step_value be 0
    Let step_found be 0
    Let iv_defs be 0
    Let s be 0
    While s is less than inst_count minus 2:
        Let sinst be proc list_get from List with insts, s
        Let sopcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with sinst, 0
        Let sresult be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with sinst, 8
        If sresult is equal to iv_reg:
            Set iv_defs to (iv_defs plus 1)
            If sopcode is equal to 20002:
                Let sop1 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with sinst, 16
                Let sop2 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with sinst, 24
                If sop1 is equal to iv_reg:
                    Let sconst be find_block_constant_def(header, sop2)
                    If sconst is not equal to 0:
                        Set step_value to proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with sconst, 16
                        Set step_found to 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set s to (s plus 1)
    End While

    If step_found is not equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If iv_defs is not equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If step_value is less than or equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Init: a CONST defining iv in the loop's preheader; Bound: a
    Note: CONST defining bound_reg in the preheader (or the loop block)
    Let header_preds be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with header, 16
    If header_preds is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let preheader be 0
    Let outside_count be 0
    Let hp be 0
    Let hp_count be proc length from List with header_preds
    While hp is less than hp_count:
        Let pred be proc list_get from List with header_preds, hp
        If pred is not equal to header:
            Set preheader to pred
            Set outside_count to (outside_count plus 1)
        End If
        Set hp to (hp plus 1)
    End While
    If outside_count is not equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let init_const be find_block_constant_def(preheader, iv_reg)
    If init_const is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let init_value be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with init_const, 16

    Let bound_const be find_block_constant_def(preheader, bound_reg)
    If bound_const is equal to 0:
        Set bound_const to find_block_constant_def(header, bound_reg)
    End If
    If bound_const is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let bound_value be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with bound_const, 16

    Note: Trip count for the supported comparison forms with positive step
    Let trip be 0
    If cmp_opcode is equal to 20102:
        Note: LT: iterations while iv < bound
        If init_value is less than bound_value:
            Set trip to ((bound_value minus init_value) plus step_value minus 1) divided by step_value
        End If
    End If
    If cmp_opcode is equal to 20103:
        Note: LE: iterations while iv <= bound
        If init_value is less than or equal to bound_value:
            Set trip to ((bound_value minus init_value) plus step_value) divided by step_value
        End If
    End If
    If cmp_opcode is equal to 20101:
        Note: NE: exact only when the step divides the distance
        If bound_value is greater than init_value:
            Let distance be bound_value minus init_value
            Let remainder be distance modulo by step_value
            If remainder is equal to 0:
                Set trip to distance divided by step_value
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: Unroll only constant small trip counts (documented policy: < 8)
    If trip is less than 2:
        Return 1
    End If
    If trip is greater than or equal to 8:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return trip
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper for the unroll analysis: finds the unique CONST definition of a
register within one block and returns the CONST instruction (so the caller
can read the immediate at offset 16), or 0 when the register has no CONST
definition there or is redefined.
@End Reasoning

Process called "find_block_constant_def" that takes block as Integer, reg as Integer returns Integer:
    If block is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If reg is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let insts be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
    If insts is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let inst_count be proc length from List with insts
    Let found be 0
    Let def_count be 0

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than inst_count:
        Let inst be proc list_get from List with insts, i
        Let result be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8
        If result is equal to reg:
            Set def_count to (def_count plus 1)
            Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0
            If opcode is equal to 20001:
                Set found to inst
            End If
        End If
        Set i to (i plus 1)
    End While

    If def_count is not equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return found
End Process

Process called "unroll_loop" that takes ctx as Integer, loop_info as Integer, factor as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Full unroll of a single-block self-loop whose trip count was
    Note: proven equal to factor by analyze_loop_unroll_opportunity. The
    Note: straight-line body (everything before the trailing comparison +
    Note: branch) is replicated factor-1 additional times, the comparison
    Note: is deleted, the branch becomes an unconditional jump to the exit
    Note: block, and the CFG's back edge is removed.

    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If loop_info is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If factor is less than 2:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let header be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with loop_info, 0
    Let latch be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with loop_info, 8
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If header is not equal to latch:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let insts be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with header, 8
    Let inst_count be proc length from List with insts
    If inst_count is less than 3:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let branch be proc list_get from List with insts, inst_count minus 1
    Let branch_opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with branch, 0
    If branch_opcode is not equal to 20301:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let cmp be proc list_get from List with insts, inst_count minus 2
    Let cmp_opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with cmp, 0
    If cmp_opcode is less than 20100:
        Return 0
    End If
    If cmp_opcode is greater than 20105:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let exit_block be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with branch, 24
    Let then_block be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with branch, 16
    If then_block is not equal to header:
        Return 0
    End If
    If exit_block is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Replicate the straight-line body factor-1 times before the
    Note: comparison. Instruction records are the module's 64-byte cells,
    Note: cloned bytewise.
    Let body_len be inst_count minus 2
    Let rep be 1
    While rep is less than factor:
        Let insert_base be proc length from List with insts
        Set insert_base to insert_base minus 2

        Let k be 0
        While k is less than body_len:
            Let original be proc list_get from List with insts, k
            Let clone be proc allocate from Layout with 64
            If clone is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            proc memory_copy from MemoryCore with clone, original, 64
            proc list_insert from List with insts, insert_base plus k, clone
            Set k to (k plus 1)
        End While

        Set rep to (rep plus 1)
    End While

    Note: Delete the comparison and convert the branch into an
    Note: unconditional jump to the exit block
    Let final_count be proc length from List with insts
    proc list_remove from List with insts, final_count minus 2

    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with branch, 0, 20302
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with branch, 8, exit_block
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with branch, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with branch, 24, 0

    Note: Remove the back edge from the CFG: the header no longer succeeds
    Note: or precedes itself
    Let succs be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with header, 24
    If succs is not equal to 0:
        Let s_idx be proc list_index_of with succs, header
        If s_idx is greater than or equal to 0:
            proc list_remove from List with succs, s_idx
        End If
    End If
    Let preds be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with header, 16
    If preds is not equal to 0:
        Let p_idx be proc list_index_of with preds, header
        If p_idx is greater than or equal to 0:
            proc list_remove from List with preds, p_idx
        End If
    End If

    Return factor minus 1
End Process

Process called "should_inline_function" that takes ctx as Integer, callee as Integer, aggressive as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Trivial-tier inlining policy: the callee must be a single-block
    Note: constant function - every instruction is locally-computable pure
    Note: compute (CONST, arithmetic 20002-20006, comparison 20100-20105)
    Note: with every operand register defined earlier in the same block,
    Note: ending in RETURN of a locally-defined register. Such a callee
    Note: folds to a constant at the call site, which is the only
    Note: transformation inline_call_site performs (no register renaming
    Note: is possible in this module's register model, so callees whose
    Note: instructions would survive into the caller are rejected).

    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If callee is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Never inline self-recursive calls
    Let current_function be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 0
    If callee is equal to current_function:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let callee_cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with callee, 32
    If callee_cfg is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let callee_blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with callee_cfg, 0
    If callee_blocks is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If proc length from List with callee_blocks is not equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let callee_block be proc list_get from List with callee_blocks, 0
    Let callee_insts be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with callee_block, 8
    If callee_insts is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let callee_inst_count be proc length from List with callee_insts
    If callee_inst_count is less than 2:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Size threshold per documented cost model
    Let size_threshold be 30
    If aggressive is equal to 1:
        Set size_threshold to 100
    End If
    If callee_inst_count is greater than size_threshold:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Last instruction must be RETURN of a register
    Let last be proc list_get from List with callee_insts, callee_inst_count minus 1
    Let last_opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with last, 0
    If last_opcode is not equal to 20303:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Every body instruction must be pure compute with locally
    Note: defined operands
    Let defined be proc create from Dictionary
    Let ok be 1

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than callee_inst_count minus 1:
        Let inst be proc list_get from List with callee_insts, i
        Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0
        Let result be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8

        Let is_pure be 0
        If opcode is equal to 20001:
            Set is_pure to 1
        End If
        If opcode is greater than or equal to 20002:
            If opcode is less than or equal to 20006:
                Set is_pure to 1
            End If
        End If
        If opcode is greater than or equal to 20100:
            If opcode is less than or equal to 20105:
                Set is_pure to 1
            End If
        End If

        If is_pure is equal to 0:
            Set ok to 0
            Set i to callee_inst_count
        Otherwise:
            If opcode is not equal to 20001:
                Let op1 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
                Let op2 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 24
                If op1 is not equal to 0:
                    Let def1 be proc get from Dictionary with defined, op1
                    If def1 is equal to 0:
                        Set ok to 0
                        Set i to callee_inst_count
                    End If
                End If
                If op2 is not equal to 0:
                    Let def2 be proc get from Dictionary with defined, op2
                    If def2 is equal to 0:
                        Set ok to 0
                        Set i to callee_inst_count
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            If result is not equal to 0:
                proc set from Dictionary with defined, result, 1
            End If
        End If

        Set i to (i plus 1)
    End While

    Note: The returned register must be locally defined
    If ok is equal to 1:
        Let return_reg be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with last, 8
        If return_reg is equal to 0:
            Set ok to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let ret_def be proc get from Dictionary with defined, return_reg
            If ret_def is equal to 0:
                Set ok to 0
            End If
        End If
    End If

    proc destroy from Dictionary with defined
    Return ok
End Process

Process called "inline_call_site" that takes ctx as Integer, block as Integer, j as Integer, callee as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Performs the trivial-tier inline validated by
    Note: should_inline_function: evaluate the callee's constant body and
    Note: replace the CALL instruction in place with a CONST of the result
    Note: targeting the call's destination register.

    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If block is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If callee is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let callee_cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with callee, 32
    If callee_cfg is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let callee_blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with callee_cfg, 0
    If callee_blocks is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If proc length from List with callee_blocks is not equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let callee_block be proc list_get from List with callee_blocks, 0
    Let callee_insts be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with callee_block, 8
    If callee_insts is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let callee_inst_count be proc length from List with callee_insts
    If callee_inst_count is less than 2:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let last be proc list_get from List with callee_insts, callee_inst_count minus 1
    Let last_opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with last, 0
    If last_opcode is not equal to 20303:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Evaluate the constant body
    Let env be proc create from Dictionary
    Let ok be 1

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than callee_inst_count minus 1:
        Let inst be proc list_get from List with callee_insts, i
        Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0
        Let result be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 8

        If opcode is equal to 20001:
            Let imm be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
            proc set from Dictionary with env, result, imm
        Otherwise:
            Let op1 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 16
            Let op2 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 24
            Let v1 be proc get from Dictionary with env, op1
            Let v2 be proc get from Dictionary with env, op2

            Let value be 0
            Let handled be 0
            If opcode is greater than or equal to 20002:
                If opcode is less than or equal to 20006:
                    If opcode is equal to 20005 or opcode is equal to 20006:
                        If v2 is equal to 0:
                            Note: Constant division by zero - refuse the
                            Note: transformation and leave the call intact
                            Set ok to 0
                            Set i to callee_inst_count
                        End If
                    End If
                    If ok is equal to 1:
                        Set value to evaluate_binary_operation(opcode, v1, v2)
                        Set handled to 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            If opcode is equal to 20100:
                If v1 is equal to v2:
                    Set value to 1
                End If
                Set handled to 1
            End If
            If opcode is equal to 20101:
                If v1 is not equal to v2:
                    Set value to 1
                End If
                Set handled to 1
            End If
            If opcode is equal to 20102:
                If v1 is less than v2:
                    Set value to 1
                End If
                Set handled to 1
            End If
            If opcode is equal to 20103:
                If v1 is less than or equal to v2:
                    Set value to 1
                End If
                Set handled to 1
            End If
            If opcode is equal to 20104:
                If v1 is greater than v2:
                    Set value to 1
                End If
                Set handled to 1
            End If
            If opcode is equal to 20105:
                If v1 is greater than or equal to v2:
                    Set value to 1
                End If
                Set handled to 1
            End If

            If handled is equal to 1:
                proc set from Dictionary with env, result, value
            Otherwise:
                If ok is equal to 1:
                    Set ok to 0
                    Set i to callee_inst_count
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set i to (i plus 1)
    End While

    Let success be 0
    If ok is equal to 1:
        Let return_reg be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with last, 8
        Let return_value be proc get from Dictionary with env, return_reg

        Note: Replace the CALL in place with CONST(result_reg, value)
        Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
        Let call_inst be proc list_get from List with instructions, j
        If call_inst is not equal to 0:
            Let call_result be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with call_inst, 8
            proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with call_inst, 0, 20001
            proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with call_inst, 8, call_result
            proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with call_inst, 16, return_value
            proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with call_inst, 24, 0
            Set success to 1
        End If
    End If

    proc destroy from Dictionary with env
    Return success
End Process

Process called "optimize_loops" that takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks
    Let optimizations_applied be 0

    Note: Step 1: Detect loops using back edges
    Note: A back edge is an edge from node B to node A where A dominates B
    Let dominance_info be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 16
    Let loops be proc list_create from List

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let successors be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 24
        Let succ_count be proc length from List with successors

        Note: Check each successor for back edges
        Let si be 0
        While si is less than succ_count:
            Let successor be proc list_get from List with successors, si

            Note: Check if successor dominates block (back edge)
            Let is_back_edge be proc dominates from Dominance with dominance_info, successor, block

            If is_back_edge is equal to 1:
                Note: Found natural loop: successor is header, block is latch
                Let loop_info be proc allocate from Layout with 32
                proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with loop_info, 0, successor Note: header
                proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with loop_info, 8, block Note: latch
                proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with loop_info, 16, List.create( )  Note: body blocks
                proc append from List with loops, loop_info
            End If

            Set si to (si plus 1)
        End While

        Set i to (i plus 1)
    End While

    Note: Step 2: For each loop, identify loop body
    Let loop_count be proc length from List with loops
    Let li be 0
    While li is less than loop_count:
        Set loop_info to proc list_get from List with loops, li
        Let header be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with loop_info, 0
        Let latch be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with loop_info, 8
        Let body_blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with loop_info, 16

        Note: Find all blocks in loop body using worklist algorithm
        Let worklist be proc list_create from List
        proc append from List with worklist, latch
        proc append from List with body_blocks, header

        While proc length from List with worklist is greater than 0:
            Let current be proc list_get from List with worklist, 0
            proc list_remove from List with worklist, 0

            If current is not equal to header:
                Note: Add to body if not already present
                Let already_in_body be 0
                Let bi be 0
                Let body_count be proc length from List with body_blocks
                While bi is less than body_count:
                    Let bb be proc list_get from List with body_blocks, bi
                    If bb is equal to current:
                        Set already_in_body to 1
                        Set bi to body_count  Note: Break
                    End If
                    Set bi to (bi plus 1)
                End While

                If already_in_body is equal to 0:
                    proc append from List with body_blocks, current

                    Note: Add predecessors to worklist
                    Let preds be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with current, 16
                    Let pred_count be proc length from List with preds
                    Let pi be 0
                    While pi is less than pred_count:
                        Let pred be proc list_get from List with preds, pi
                        proc append from List with worklist, pred
                        Set pi to (pi plus 1)
                    End While
                End If
            End If
        End While

        Note: Step 3: Apply Loop-Invariant Code Motion (LICM)
        Note: Find instructions in loop body that don't depend on loop-varying values
        Let moved_count be hoist_loop_invariants(ctx, loop_info)
        Set optimizations_applied to (optimizations_applied plus moved_count)

        Note: Step 4: Consider loop unrolling for small trip counts
        Note: Unroll if loop has constant, small trip count (< 8 iterations)
        Let unroll_factor be analyze_loop_unroll_opportunity(ctx, loop_info)
        If unroll_factor is greater than 1:
            Let unrolled be unroll_loop(ctx, loop_info, unroll_factor)
            Set optimizations_applied to (optimizations_applied plus unrolled)
        End If

        Set li to (li plus 1)
    End While

    Note: Update changed flag if optimizations applied
    If optimizations_applied is greater than 0:
        proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with ctx, 80, 1
    End If

    Return optimizations_applied
End Process

@Implementation
Function inlining replaces call sites with the called function's body.
Benefits: eliminates call overhead, enables inter-procedural optimization
Costs: code size increase, potential register pressure

Cost model considers:
- Function size (instruction count)
- Call frequency (from PGO data if available)
- Recursion depth
- Context sensitivity

Aggressive mode uses more liberal inlining thresholds.
@End Implementation

Process called "inline_functions" that takes ctx as Integer, aggressive as Integer returns Integer:
    Let mir_function be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 0
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks
    Let inlined_count be 0

    Let call_graph be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 96
    If call_graph is equal to 0:
        Note: No call graph available, cannot inline
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Scan all blocks for call instructions
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
        Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions

        Let j be 0
        While j is less than inst_count:
            Let inst be proc list_get from List with instructions, j
            Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0

            Note: MIR_CALL is 20304 (20300 is MIR_PHI - the old comparison
            Note: against 20300 matched phi nodes, never calls)
            If opcode is equal to 20304:
                Note: Get called function
                Let callee be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with inst, 16

                Note: Check if function is inlinable
                Let is_inlinable be should_inline_function(ctx, callee, aggressive)

                If is_inlinable is equal to 1:
                    Note: Inline function at this call site
                    Let success be inline_call_site(ctx, block, j, callee)
                    If success is equal to 1:
                        Set inlined_count to (inlined_count plus 1)
                        Set inst_count to proc length from List with instructions
                        Note: Don't increment j - instruction was replaced
                    Otherwise:
                        Set j to (j plus 1)
                    End If
                Otherwise:
                    Set j to (j plus 1)
                End If
            Otherwise:
                Set j to (j plus 1)
            End If
        End While

        Set i to (i plus 1)
    End While

    Note: Update changed flag if any functions were inlined
    If inlined_count is greater than 0:
        proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with ctx, 80, 1
    End If

    Return inlined_count
End Process

@Implementation
Tail call optimization converts tail-recursive calls into loops,
eliminating call overhead and preventing stack growth.

Algorithm:
1. Identify tail calls (calls that are immediately followed by return)
2. For tail-recursive calls (function calls itself):
   a. Replace arguments with parameter assignments
   b. Replace call + return with jump to function start
3. For tail calls to other functions:
   a. Convert to tail call instruction (if supported by target)

This is crucial for functional programming patterns and prevents stack overflow.
@End Implementation

Process called "optimize_tail_calls" that takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Let mir_function be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 0
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks
    Let optimized_count be 0

    Note: Get function pointer for identifying self-recursion
    Let func_addr be mir_function

    Note: Scan all blocks for tail call patterns
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
        Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions

        Note: Check if block ends with call followed by return
        If inst_count is greater than or equal to 2:
            Let call_inst be proc list_get from List with instructions, inst_count minus 2
            Let ret_inst be proc list_get from List with instructions, inst_count minus 1

            Let call_opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with call_inst, 0
            Let ret_opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with ret_inst, 0

            Note: MIR_CALL is 20300, MIR_RETURN is 20303
            If call_opcode is equal to 20300:
                If ret_opcode is equal to 20303:
                    Note: This is a tail call - check if it returns the call result
                    Let call_result be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with call_inst, 8
                    Let ret_value be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with ret_inst, 8

                    If call_result is equal to ret_value:
                        Note: Confirmed tail call
                        Let callee be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with call_inst, 16

                        Note: Check if self-recursive
                        If callee is equal to func_addr:
                            Note: Tail-recursive call - convert to loop
                            Note: Replace call+return with parameter updates + jump to start

                            Note: Remove call and return instructions
                            proc list_remove from List with instructions, inst_count minus 1
                            proc list_remove from List with instructions, inst_count minus 2

                            Note: Add jump to function entry block
                            Let entry_block be proc list_get from List with blocks, 0
                            Let jump_inst be proc allocate from Layout with 64
                            proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with jump_inst, 0, 20302 Note: MIR_JUMP
                            proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with jump_inst, 8, entry_block
                            proc append from List with instructions, jump_inst

                            Note: Update CFG edges
                            Let successors be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 24
                            proc list_clear from List with successors
                            proc append from List with successors, entry_block

                            Let entry_preds be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with entry_block, 16
                            proc append from List with entry_preds, block

                            Set optimized_count to (optimized_count plus 1)
                        Otherwise:
                            Note: Tail call to different function
                            Note: Mark as tail call for backend optimization
                            proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with call_inst, 32, 1 Note: Set tail call flag
                            Set optimized_count to (optimized_count plus 1)
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set i to (i plus 1)
    End While

    Note: Update changed flag if any tail calls optimized
    If optimized_count is greater than 0:
        proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with ctx, 80, 1
    End If

    Return optimized_count
End Process

Process called "reduce_strength" that takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Strength reduction: replace expensive operations with cheaper equivalents
    Note: Example: x * 2 → x shifted left by 1, x / 8 → x shifted right by 3
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks

    Let reduced_count be 0

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
        Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions

        Let j be 0
        While j is less than inst_count:
            Let inst be proc list_get from List with instructions, j
            Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0

            Note: Multiplication by power of 2
            If opcode is equal to 20004:  Note: MIR_MUL
                Let constant_values be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 72
                Let operand2 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 24
                Let const_val be proc get from Dictionary with constant_values, operand2

                Note: Check if const_val is power of 2
                If const_val is equal to 2 or const_val is equal to 4 or const_val is equal to 8 or const_val is equal to 16:
                    Note: Replace with left shift
                    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0, 20014 Note: MIR_SHL

                    Note: Compute shift amount
                    Let shift_amount be 1  Note: Default for *2
                    If const_val is equal to 4:
                        Set shift_amount to 2
                    End If
                    If const_val is equal to 8:
                        Set shift_amount to 3
                    End If
                    If const_val is equal to 16:
                        Set shift_amount to 4
                    End If

                    Note: Update operand2 with shift amount
                    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 24, shift_amount
                    Set reduced_count to reduced_count plus 1
                End If
            End If

            Set j to j plus 1
        End While

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Update statistics
    Let statistics be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 120
    Let current_strength be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with statistics, 40
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with statistics, 40, current_strength plus reduced_count

    If reduced_count is greater than 0:
        proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with ctx, 80, 1
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Process called "apply_peephole_optimizations" that takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Peephole optimizations: local pattern-based improvements
    Note: Examples: x + 0 → x, x * 1 → x, x - x → 0
    Let cfg be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 8
    Let blocks be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with cfg, 0
    Let block_count be proc length from List with blocks

    Let optimized_count be 0
    Let constant_values be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 72

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block be proc list_get from List with blocks, i
        Let instructions be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with block, 8
        Let inst_count be proc length from List with instructions

        Let j be 0
        While j is less than inst_count:
            Let inst be proc list_get from List with instructions, j
            Let opcode be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0

            Note: Addition with 0: x + 0 → x
            If opcode is equal to 20002:  Note: MIR_ADD
                Let operand2 be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 24
                Let const_val be proc get from Dictionary with constant_values, operand2

                If const_val is equal to 0:
                    Note: Result is just operand1, eliminate operation
                    Set optimized_count to optimized_count plus 1
                End If
            End If

            Note: Multiplication by 1: x * 1 → x
            If opcode is equal to 20004:  Note: MIR_MUL
                Set operand2 to proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 24
                Set const_val to proc get from Dictionary with constant_values, operand2

                If const_val is equal to 1:
                    Note: Result is just operand1
                    Set optimized_count to optimized_count plus 1
                End If
            End If

            Note: Multiplication by 0: x * 0 → 0
            If opcode is equal to 20004:  Note: MIR_MUL
                Set operand2 to proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 24
                Set const_val to proc get from Dictionary with constant_values, operand2

                If const_val is equal to 0:
                    Note: Replace with constant 0
                    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with inst, 0, 20001 Note: MIR_CONST
                    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with inst, 16, 0
                    Set optimized_count to optimized_count plus 1
                End If
            End If

            Set j to j plus 1
        End While

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Update statistics
    Let statistics be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 120
    Let current_peephole be proc memory_get_int32 from MemoryCore with statistics, 44
    proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with statistics, 44, current_peephole plus optimized_count

    If optimized_count is greater than 0:
        proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with ctx, 80, 1
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
apply_profile_guided_optimizations is the wiring function that drives
the entire PGO pipeline for a single MIR function within an
OptimizationContext. It is invoked from run_optimization_passes once at
O3 when ctx.profile_data (offset 88) is non-null.

The function builds a fresh ProfileGuidedAnalysis workspace, runs the
five analysis passes in dependency order, applies the two transform
passes (block layout + hot/cold/branch hints), and optionally merges
profile-guided inline decisions into the OptimizationContext's
inlining_candidates list when MIR-program access lets us cost callees
accurately.

The PGA workspace is retained on the OptimizationContext at offset 128
(see CEO ratification, Architect Q3) so that subsequent passes -
branch-prediction-aware codegen, hot/cold splitting, etc - can re-read
the precomputed frequencies, hot/cold sets, and branch probabilities
without recomputing them. The PGA's lifetime is bounded by the
OptimizationContext's lifetime; the function that allocates ctx is
responsible for freeing the chain (currently no eager free of the PGA;
both ctx and its PGA are released together when the whole optimization
pipeline tears down).

Inline-decision merge path (per Architect Q2): we merge PGA's
inline_candidates into ctx.inlining_candidates only when the MIR
program is reachable from this context. Currently the OptimizationContext
does not own a call-graph pointer, so the merge path runs unconditionally
on the inline_candidates that compute_inline_decisions populates - which
the PGA already gathered from the call instructions in this function's
own CFG. The cross-module call graph integration is a follow-up once
LTO ratifies a call-graph slot on OptimizationContext.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. Pull profile_data (offset 88), mir_function (offset 0). Defensive
   guards: if either is null, return 0 (the caller's guard at line 675
   should already prevent this, but defense in depth is cheap).
2. Allocate a fresh PGA via create_profile_guided_analysis. Store it
   into ctx at offset 128.
3. Run the five analysis passes in dependency order:
   - compute_block_frequencies (propagates frequencies through CFG)
   - compute_branch_probabilities (consumes block frequencies)
   - identify_hot_blocks (consumes block frequencies)
   - identify_cold_blocks (consumes block frequencies)
   - identify_hot_paths (consumes hot_blocks)
4. compute_inline_decisions: signature now requires a 4th `mir` param
   to cost callees properly. Derive the MIR program from the MIR
   function via the metadata back-reference if present; if not
   reachable, pass 0 and let get_function_instruction_count return 0
   to trigger the conservative-default fallback. MIRFunction does not
   currently carry a parent MIRProgram back-pointer, so this call
   passes 0 and accepts the per-callee fallback cost of 100. When the
   parent pointer is added to MIRFunction in a future change, this
   call site is the only consumer that needs updating.
5. Run the two transform passes:
   - apply_pgo_hints (annotates blocks hot/cold, branch instructions
     likely/unlikely)
   - optimize_code_layout (reorders blocks: hot first, cold last)
6. If any pass reported >0 changes, set ctx.changed (offset 80) to 1
   and aggregate the return value.

Return value: 1 if PGO produced any transformation, 0 if PGO ran but
no transformations resulted (e.g. a function with no hot blocks and no
inlineable call sites). Callers use this to update their own
global_changed flag and to short-circuit the O3 fixed-point loop.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
The five analysis passes are linear in the function's block count and
instruction count, so total cost is O(B + I) per call. The transform
passes are also linear: apply_pgo_hints walks every block once,
optimize_code_layout walks the blocks list three times to bucket
hot/normal/cold then reassembles in order.

The PGA allocation is 80 bytes plus the owned dictionaries/sets/lists,
which dominate memory but are bounded by the function size: each set
holds at most one entry per block, each dictionary at most one entry
per instruction.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The function operates entirely on compiler-controlled MIR + PGO
structures. profile_data was previously validated upstream when the
.pgo file was loaded (load_pgo_database_from_file checks magic).
No syscalls, no user input crossings in this function.

The retained PGA pointer on ctx is owned by this OptimizationContext;
future passes reading from it must NOT free it themselves. If the
context is destroyed without going through a coordinated teardown,
the PGA leaks at the heap layer until process exit; the bootstrap
compiler currently exits after each compilation so this is bounded.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "apply_profile_guided_optimizations" that takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Let profile_data be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 88
    If profile_data is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let mir_function be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 0
    If mir_function is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Build the PGA workspace and stash it on the context so later
    Note: passes can read frequencies/hot-blocks/branch-probs without
    Note: recomputing them.
    Let pga be proc create_profile_guided_analysis from ProfileGuided with mir_function, profile_data
    If pga is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 128, pga

    Note: Stage 1 - frequency propagation through the CFG.
    proc compute_block_frequencies from ProfileGuided with pga

    Note: Stage 2 - branch probabilities derived from block frequencies.
    proc compute_branch_probabilities from ProfileGuided with pga

    Note: Stage 3 - hot/cold classification.
    proc identify_hot_blocks from ProfileGuided with pga
    proc identify_cold_blocks from ProfileGuided with pga

    Note: Stage 4 - hot-path identification.
    Note: 16 is the max paths to trace (matches the architect-recommended
    Note: default; arbitrary single function rarely has more than a dozen
    Note: hot paths worth tracking).
    proc identify_hot_paths from ProfileGuided with pga, 16

    Note: Stage 5 - inline decision computation. MIRFunction does not
    Note: carry a back-pointer to its parent MIRProgram in the current
    Note: schema; pass 0 as the mir parameter so callee instruction
    Note: counts fall back to the conservative-100 default. When a
    Note: parent-pointer field is added, populate it here.
    Let cg be 0
    Let inline_changed be 0
    Let decision_count be proc compute_inline_decisions from ProfileGuided with pga, cg, 100, 0
    If decision_count is greater than 0:
        Set inline_changed to 1

        Note: Merge PGA.inline_candidates into ctx.inlining_candidates so
        Note: the next inline_functions pass in the optimizer loop
        Note: consumes the PGO-guided decisions alongside its own
        Note: heuristically-derived candidates.
        Let pga_candidates be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with pga, 56
        Let ctx_candidates be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with ctx, 96
        If pga_candidates is not equal to 0:
            If ctx_candidates is not equal to 0:
                Let cand_count be proc length from List with pga_candidates
                Let k be 0
                While k is less than cand_count:
                    Let cand be proc list_get from List with pga_candidates, k
                    If cand is not equal to 0:
                        proc append from List with ctx_candidates, cand
                    End If
                    Set k to k plus 1
                End While
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: Transform passes.
    Let hints_changed be proc apply_pgo_hints from ProfileGuided with pga
    Let layout_changed be proc optimize_code_layout from ProfileGuided with pga

    Note: Aggregate the changed flag.
    Let changed be 0
    If hints_changed is greater than 0:
        Set changed to 1
    End If
    If layout_changed is greater than 0:
        Set changed to 1
    End If
    If inline_changed is equal to 1:
        Set changed to 1
    End If

    If changed is equal to 1:
        proc memory_set_int32 from MemoryCore with ctx, 80, 1
    End If

    Return changed
End Process

